episodes.overview: The five contestants facing elimination this weekhave to create their own breakfast dish and then serve it in just an hour to 100 hungry customers.

episodes.name: Masterclass 9
episodes.overview: Kirsten Tibballs shows how to make an indulgent chocolate dessert perfect perfect for sharing. Gary creates a gorgeous dessert to tempt your loved one.

episodes.name: Heston Blumenthal Week Day 1: Royal Jubilee Trifle
episodes.overview: The judges are joined by Heston Blumenthal and the contestants have two hours to recreate Heston’s royal jubilee trifle as they battle it out to win immunity.

episodes.name: Heston Blumenthal Week Day 2: Cook Against Heston Immunity
episodes.overview: The three winning contestants are given just 90 minutes to cook either an entrée, main or dessert while Heston has to cook all three courses in the same time. There is a twist in the challenge though.

episodes.name: Heston Blumenthal Week Day 3: Medieval Knights Feast
episodes.overview: The teams have two and a half hours to create a Heston-esque medieval feast for ten noble knights and the judges.

episodes.name: Heston Blumenthal Week Day 4: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants from the losing team battle it out in today’s elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Masterclass 10
episodes.overview: Heston offers a masterclass on how to create perfect scrambled eggs. He also creates a roasted leg of lamb with anchovies and rosemary and demonstrates how to carve for maximum flavour.

episodes.name: World Food Week Day 1: VIP Banquet
episodes.overview: The remaining eight contestants are flown to Dubai and split into four teams of two the contestants to face a challenge that sees them shop in the local Souk Markets and then create a banquet to 36 VIP's.

episodes.name: World Food Week Day 2: Palms Hotel Elimination
episodes.overview: The 6 losing contestants from yesterday’s challenge are put in charge of the Ossiano kitchen at The Palms Hotel Atlantis, where they have to create dinner for 50 VIP Atlantis guests as well as Ossiano Vice President, Mark Patten.

episodes.name: World Food Week Day 3: Mexico or China
episodes.overview: The contestants are split into two teams and have to create a lunchtime menu for city based office workers in Melbourne composed of dishes from either Mexico or China.

episodes.name: World Food Week Day 4: Qantas World Map of Food
episodes.overview: The contestants find themselves standing in front of the Qantas World Map of Food. They then have to create dishes from various regions of the world.

episodes.name: Masterclass 11
episodes.overview: The two lucky contestants who won Sunday night’s challenge are flown first class to Paris where Matt Preston shows them some of his favourite places to eat.

episodes.name: Dreams Week Day 1: Service Challenge
episodes.overview: The seven remaining contestants begin to realise that their food dreams are a real possibility. The service challenge sees them having to create dinner for some very surprise guests.

episodes.name: Dreams Week Day 2: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Those facing elimination need to create cook a plate of food that demonstrates their food dream.

episodes.name: Dreams Week Day 3: Josie Bones
episodes.overview: The final six contestants pay a visit to Josie Bones, a restaurant owned by Chris Badenoch, who was a former Masterchef contestant. They are split into teams and have to create three dishes to serve to Chris' customers with the worst team having to face the next elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Dreams Week Day 4: Darren's Raspberry Rhubarb Ginger Chocolate Dessert.
episodes.overview: The contestants facing elimination have to try and replicate Darren Purchase’s, raspberry rhubarb ginger chocolate dessert.

episodes.name: Masterclass 12
episodes.overview: Annie Smithers and John Reid are with the top five contestants & the judges, to create some great regional country produce.

episodes.name: Finals Week Day 1: Mystery Box
episodes.overview: The latest mystery box challenge sees the contestants being given 10 ingredients, five chosen by the contestants and the other five chosen by the judges. They then have just sixty minutes to create a delicious meal.

episodes.name: Finals Week Day 2: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The five contestants are matched with a chef that has a style and expertise to match their culinary ambitions in the latest elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Finals Week Day 3: The Atlantic Service Challenge
episodes.overview: The four hopefuls left in the running arrive at Donovan Cooke’s restaurant, The Atlantic. Each of them have to create a two course meal chosen by Donovan for some VIP Atlantic customers.

episodes.name: Finals Week Day 4: Culinary Dueling
episodes.overview: The hopefuls battle it out in a culinary duel over three different rounds. In eachround, they have just thirty minutes and an open pantry to try and come up with their winning dishes. At the end of the show there is another elimination.

episodes.name: Masterclass 13
episodes.overview: All of the contestants from this year's competition return to take part in the last Masterclass of the season. The tables are turned though as they set a mystery box challenge for George and Gary.

episodes.name: Grandfinal
episodes.overview: The finalists battle it out to secure the $100,000 cash prize, an Alfa Romeo Giulietta, a cookbook deal with New Holland and access to Australia’s best kitchens.

episodes.name: Series 6 Premiere
episodes.overview: MasterChef Australia returns with the best group of home cooks the competition has ever seen. In the first episode, our potential contestants are given one hour to cook their best dish and secure their spot in the top 24.

episodes.name: Top 50: Core Skills Invention Test
episodes.overview: Just 10 aprons remain for the 18 remaining aspiring home cooks.The contestants are put through their paces in a core skills invention test, then, contestants must recreate George Calombaris' superb lemon lime and bitters dessert.

episodes.name: Top 24: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: The top 24 contestants enter the MasterChef Australia kitchen for the very first time. First up tonight, the contestants face the classic mystery box challenge, but there's a surprise in store.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Chinese Fried Rice
episodes.overview: In tonight's elimination episode, 21 contestants face elimination for the first time with a three-round challenge. The contestants are given just 30 minutes to cook a perfect Chinese fried rice. Who will be the first contestant to go?

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge and Breakfast Invention Test
episodes.overview: The 21 contestants enter the kitchen to find a mystery box at their bench. They have one hour to cook a dish using at least one of the ingredients.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Shannon Bennett's Fillet of Beef
episodes.overview: The three contestants with the least impressive dishes from the invention test face off in the pressure test. They are given the challenge of re-creating guest chef Shannon Bennett's fillet of beef with a bone marrow crust.

episodes.name: Off-Site Challenge: Lunch Service in St Kilda
episodes.overview: In the season's first off-site challenge, the contestants split into two teams for a lunch service challenge at two popular St Kilda restaurants. The team with the most money in the till at the end of the challenge wins.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Three Dishes from One Snapper
episodes.overview: The losing team from last night's challenge are all facing elimination and have to plan three dishes from one snapper. In an unexpected twist, one contestant takes the biggest risk in the history of MasterChef Australia. Will it pay off?

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Maggie Beer
episodes.overview: In a special episode, the queen of the Australian kitchen, Maggie Beer, returns to the kitchen for the Mystery Box challenge. Who will impress the judges in the challenge?

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Alla Wolf-Tasker's Rivers and Lakes
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the Invention Test face off in the Pressure Test. Who will be hanging up their apron and leaving the MasterChef kitchen for the last time?

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Ollie Gould & Kylie Kwong
episodes.overview: The three best performing contestants in the Invention Test get to compete for immunity. Competing against chefs Ollie Gould and Kylie Kwong, who has what it takes to win the immunity?

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Three Course Menu from Memory
episodes.overview: In this challenge it's all about strategy, memory, communication, pace and teamwork as the contestants are split into two teams. However, as always, there's a twist.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge in Three Rounds
episodes.overview: The losing team from the latest challenge now face off over three rounds. By the end of round three, one of the 10 contestants will be eliminated from the competition.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge and Invention Test
episodes.overview: A mystery box challenge quickly becomes a nightmare for some; while an invention test goes like a dream for others.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the invention test face off in a pressure test where they have three hours to replicate a complex dessert. The worst dish will be eliminated from the competition.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Benjamin Cooper
episodes.overview: The contestant playing for immunity must cook off against Benjamin Cooper from leading restaurant, Chin Chin, even with a 15-minute head start, have they got what it takes to out-cook a professional?

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Four-Course Dessert Menu
episodes.overview: The contestants are tasked to create a four-course dessert menu, with each team needing to prepare 10 serves of each dessert to the judges. Which team will go head to head in the elimination?

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Blind Taste Test
episodes.overview: The contestants from the losing team compete in a blind taste test. They must taste a mystery dish while blindfolded then recreate the dish. The worst dish will be hanging up the apron forever.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants enter the kitchen for another Mystery Box challenge, but there's a twist...The top three dishes will compete for immunity while the bottom three will face elimination.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Saint Crispin
episodes.overview: In an intense pressure test, the three contestants must recreate a dish made by the co-head chefs from leading Melbourne restaurant Saint Crispin. Who will be safe from elimination?

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Matt Stone
episodes.overview: With immunity up for grabs the three contestants battle it out with cheese. Who will get the chance to cook for immunity and go up against celebrated chef Matt Stone?

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Queen Victoria Market
episodes.overview: The contestants arrive at Melbourne's Queen Victoria Market and are tasked to work in teams at four different stalls. The team with the lowest profit will face off in the elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Time Auction
episodes.overview: The losing team from the off-site challenge will compete in a time-auction elimination challenge and one contestant's dream will be over. Also, we end with a sweet Masterclass that's all about dessert.

episodes.name: Invention Test: Chocolate
episodes.overview: In the invention test, each team has to produce one sweet and one savoury dish using chocolate, showing their versatility. The team that impresses the judges the most will win a chance at immunity.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Nobu Matsuhisa
episodes.overview: In a pressure test like no other, internationally acclaimed chef Nobu Matsuhisa sets a challenge for the losing team from the invention test in one of the toughest cooks yet.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The three best performers in the invention test are vying for immunity. However, they must produce a dish using either a blow torch, a smoking gun or a cream whip dispenser.

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge: Wedding Anniversary at Ascot House
episodes.overview: Love is in the air as the contestants arrive at Melbourne's prestigious Ascot House to celebrate a diamond jubilee wedding anniversary with no food. That's where the contestants come in.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: In a two-round elimination challenge the losing team from the off-site challenge go head-to-head to keep their place in the competition. Which amateur cook will say goodbye forever?

episodes.name: Mystery Box: Marco Pierre White
episodes.overview: The contestants are stunned to find the Godfather of modern cooking, Marco Pierre White, waiting for them. The winner of Marco's mystery box challenge gets to choose the core ingredient in the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: White Heat
episodes.overview: Marco Pierre White sets the pressure test challenge from his iconic cookbook, White Heat. Emotions run high when one contestant is sent packing forever.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Donovan Cooke
episodes.overview: The contestant cooking for immunity must match skills with Donovan Cooke from the renowned Melbourne restaurant Atlantic. Have they got what it takes to take down a professional?

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge: Taxi Kitchen
episodes.overview: The off-site challenge sees the contestants split into two teams to cook a three-course, British-inspired menu for 120 diners at Taxi Kitchen, in Melbourne's Federation Square.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Risotto
episodes.overview: Each contestant has one hour to cook a risotto, but to impress they must take this popular dish to another level. The contestant with the least impressive dish will leave the kitchen.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants enter the MasterChef Australia kitchen to find two mystery boxes, but this week these two boxes will turn the competition on its head.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Vikas Khanna
episodes.overview: In the Pressure Test Challenge, the contestants must work with chef and host of MasterChef India, Vikas Khanna. The least impressive dish will leave the competition.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Second Chances
episodes.overview: We are down to the Top Ten contestants; but this challenge will present the biggest shock in the competition so far. Only the most courageous will win.

episodes.name: Service Challenge: Starlight Children's Foundation
episodes.overview: Guest chef Curtis Stone leads the service challenge at the Starlight Children's Foundation charity lunch. The contestants are split in two teams and must raise the most money for the charity.

episodes.name: Power Apron Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: In an intense Mystery Box challenge, the winning team from the service challenge play off for the power apron, which will mean they control every challenge played out next week.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test
episodes.overview: It's power apron week and the contestant holding the apron will have a big advantage in the Mystery Box challenge and the Invention test. Which three contestants will face-off for elimination?

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Croquembouche
episodes.overview: In one of the most difficult pressure tests yet, the three contestants must battle it out to stay in the competition. However, the power apron plays a role yet again and one cook will say goodbye.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: In the immunity challenge the contestant with the power apron will compete for a chance at immunity. But will the power apron help the contestant get one over the professional chef?

episodes.name: Service Challenge: Banquet for 20 Food Producers
episodes.overview: In the service challenge, the contestants are split into two teams to cook a banquet for 20 food producers. The power apron contestant gets to choose their team members for the challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Mexican
episodes.overview: In a Mexican-themed elimination challenge, the five remaining contests will face-off to avoid elimination. However, the power apron contestant will play a vital role on who will be staying...

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Barter
episodes.overview: With the same six items in each contestant's mystery box, they all must barter with each other to get a variety of ingredients. Which three contestants will battle it out for immunity?

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Nick Palumbo's Choc-Top Ice Creams
episodes.overview: In the Pressure Test, the contestants must make four of Nick Palumbo's classic choc-top ice creams from scratch. The least impressive dish will leave the competition forever.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: John Lawson
episodes.overview: The contestants vying for immunity must identify 12 cuts of a cow. The contestant that names all 12 correctly will go up against professional chef, John Lawson. Can they out-cook a professional?

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge: Asian
episodes.overview: In an Asian cuisine challenge, the contestants, in four teams must cook an Asian dish for 200 hungry fans who have the power to decide on their favourite dishes.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Dave Verhuel
episodes.overview: The two losing teams from the team challenge must replicate a signature dish by chef Dave Verhuel without a recipe. The least impressive dish will be eliminated from the competition.

episodes.name: Mystery Box: Heston Blumenthal & Invention Test
episodes.overview: To the contestant's surprise, chef Heston Blumenthal will be heading up the challenges, starting with the first challenge and the Invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Beetroot Risotto
episodes.overview: The contestants must cook one of Heston's dishes: beetroot risotto. With no recipe, they must keep up with Heston as he cooks the dish in front of them, but they must finish cooking at the same time.

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge
episodes.overview: In the off-site challenge, Heston sets the task for the five contestants cooking. They must pimp the menu of a local Melbourne pub and run the service for 120 customers, with Heston at the helm.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Five Senses
episodes.overview: The contestants must make a dish inspired by the five senses. Each cook has to include taste and the remaining senses are allocated between the contestants to include in their dish.

episodes.name: Sudden Death Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Four contestants face off in a sudden death elimination challenge? and then an incredible Masterclass from Heston.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants open their mystery boxes and find ingredients chosen by their loved ones. They now have 45 minutes to cook something spectacular using those ingredients.

episodes.name: Invention Test
episodes.overview: In an emotional invention test, the remaining five contestants are surprised to learn that there are no rules or restraints: they can cook whatever they choose with full access to the pantry.

episodes.name: Duel Challenge Over Three Rounds
episodes.overview: The top four contestants must cook off in a duel challenge over three rounds. There's a great deal at stake as the winner of the third round will secure a place in the semi-final.

episodes.name: Service Challenge: Vue de Monde
episodes.overview: With one contestant already through to the semi-final, the remaining three contestants compete in a service challenge at the three-hatted Vue de Monde restaurant in Melbourne.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Three contestants must cook off in an elimination pressure test with one leaving forever. Also, the contestants sit the final MasterClass, joined by special guest chefs Curtis Stone and Kylie Kwong.

episodes.name: MasterChef 2014 Semi Final
episodes.overview: The stakes are high as the three remaining contestants fight for a place in the finale. Will your favourite amateur cook make it through to the final two?

episodes.name: MasterChef 2014 Finale
episodes.overview: The massive finale will be played out in a culinary duel over three rounds with the chance to win $250,000 and prizes to change their lives forever. Who will be Australia's MasterChef for 2014?

episodes.name: Auditions, Part 1
episodes.overview: Season Premiere. With the culinary bar set high in 2014, the heat will be on as MasterChef Australia returns for 2015. Home cooks from around the country begin the battle for the title of Australia's next MasterChef.

episodes.name: Auditions, Part 2
episodes.overview: In their first challenge, the contestants have 75 minutes to make a savoury dish in order to secure themselves a spot in the Top 24. Which contestants will claim the last remaining aprons?

episodes.name: Top 24 Mystery Box
episodes.overview: The Top 24 contestants enter the MasterChef Australia kitchen for their first mystery box challenge.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Massimo Bottura
episodes.overview: The contestants must break into three teams and battle it out in the first team challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Fish
episodes.overview: In today's very fishy challenge, the eight contestants from the losing team in yesterday's task must face off to stay in the competition.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test: Guilty Pleasures
episodes.overview: The mystery box is revealed as today's challenge. It is their chance to show the judges what they are made of and the winning dish will gain an advantage going into the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The three contestants with the least impressive dishes from the previous invention test face off in the pressure test. One contestant will cook their last dish in the MasterChef Australia kitchen.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Jaffle Iron
episodes.overview: Today the three best-performing contestants in the invention test will compete for immunity. The judges reveal that each contestant must first cook a sweet or savoury dish using a jaffle iron.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Two-Course Meal for the Army
episodes.overview: The remaining 22 contestants must team up and cook a two-course meal, a main and a dessert, for 120 guests made up of serving Army personnel, Legacy guests and their families.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The losing team from yesterday's challenge must cook-off to keep their place in the competition. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be eliminated from MasterChef Australia.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Five Tastes
episodes.overview: The contestants arrive at the MasterChef Australia kitchen to find Marco Pierre White there to greet them. Today's mystery box challenge is all about the five fundamental tastes in the human palate.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The three contestants with the least impressive dish from the previous invention test face off in the pressure test. At the end of the challenge, one of these contestants will be going home.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The three best performers in the invention test are vying for immunity. Marco Pierre White sets them a 30 minute challenge with unlimited pantry access.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Relay
episodes.overview: In today's challenge, the contestants are split into four teams, with each team cooking in a relay. All five members of the team with the least impressive dish will go into tomorrow's elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination & MasterClass 1
episodes.overview: In tonight's elimination, contestants must prepare a single dish plated into five identical serves, one for each of the four judges and one for the cook who will have the honour of dining with the judges. Closing out the episode with Marco Pierre White is the first MasterClass of the season. The contestants are joined by our judges at the picturesque Burnham Beeches.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: In a very special episode, the Queen of the Australian kitchen, Maggie Beer returns to the MasterChef Australia kitchen as the 19 contestants face another mystery box challenge.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The judges reveal that today's pressure test has been set by a rising star in the dessert world, guest chef Anna. The contestant with the least impressive dish will leave the competition.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: With guest mentor Shannon Bennett leading today's challenge, has our amateur MasterChef cook got what it takes to out-perform one of the best?

episodes.name: Off-site Challenge: Abbotsford Convent Bakery
episodes.overview: In an off-site team challenge, the contestants will be taking over the bakery at Melbourne's iconic Abbotsford Convent.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The losing team of nine cooks face off in the elimination challenge and the contestant with the least impressive dish in round three will leave the kitchen.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: The judges tell the 17 contestants to realise their food dreams. Plus, past contestants return to showcase their skills.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The three contestants in this episodes pressure test see former season four contestant Kylie Millar enter the kitchen. Plus, we say goodbye as one contestant will cook their last dish.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Callum Hann
episodes.overview: The three best performers in the invention test are vying for immunity. The winner of round one will cook off against season two runner-up Callum Hann.

episodes.name: Off-site Challenge: Mexican Street Food
episodes.overview: This episodes challenge is to cook Mexican street food for a huge crowd of 500 guests, with three and a half hours to prepare and ninety minutes to serve as many people as possible.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Justine Schofield & MasterClass 2
episodes.overview: The eight members of the losing team from the Mexican challenge are facing elimination. With 90 minutes on the clock and an open pantry, the contestants must re-invent a classic French dish.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: In this mystery box challenge, the contestants learn that each ingredient costs $1 or less and are given 60 minutes to create a dish using at least one ingredient.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: In a pressure test like no other, the losing team face off in one of the toughest challenges which has been set by one of the world's greatest chefs, Marcus Wareing.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Nick Holloway
episodes.overview: The contestant cooking for immunity must face off against Nick Holloway, from Nu Nu Restaurant in Palm Cove, Queensland. Has the amateur cook got what it takes to out-perform one of the best...

episodes.name: Off-site Challenge: Pizzini Wines
episodes.overview: The contestants arrive at Pizzini Wines in north-eastern Victoria's beautiful King Valley. Divided into two teams, each is set the challenge to cook a three-course Italian feast.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The losing contestants from the team challenge are cooking to stay in the competition. They enter the MasterChef Australia kitchen to find mystery boxes on their benches.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: It's power apron week on MasterChef Australia. Whoever holds the apron will have an extra advantage in the upcoming challenges. There are four chances to win and wear it across the week.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The contestants with the three least impressive dishes from the invention test face off in the pressure test. The contestant whose dish least impresses the judges will be eliminated.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: In an immunity challenge with a twist, the four best performing cooks from the invention test have a chance to fight it out for guaranteed immunity and the power apron.

episodes.name: Off-site Challenge: Tokyo Tina vs. Saigon Sally
episodes.overview: Split into two teams, the contestants will be taking over two popular Melbourne restaurants: Tokyo Tina and Saigon Sally. The losing team will go into tomorrow's elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Power Week. The elimination challenge will take place over two rounds. Firstly, the contestants perform a blind taste test and then must create a dish using only the ingredients they have correctly named.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Heston Blumenthal & Invention Test
episodes.overview: Today's mystery box challenge has been set by the great Heston Blumenthal. The contestants have 60 minutes to create a dish using at least one ingredient chosen by Heston.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Guillaume Brahimi's Jewel of the Sea
episodes.overview: The judges reveal that the pressure test has been set by celebrated chef Guillaume Brahimi, the contestants have two and a half hours to recreate Guillaume's elaborate jewel of the sea dish.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Today the three contestants who impressed in Heston Blumenthal's invention test cook for immunity. Does the amateur cook have what it takes to out-cook the professional?

episodes.name: Off-site Challenge: Afternoon Tea at The Hotel Windsor
episodes.overview: In the team challenge, contestants are split into two teams to prepare afternoon tea for 100 guests at Melbourne's The Hotel Windsor.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The five members of the losing team from yesterday's afternoon tea challenge enter the MasterChef Australia kitchen in what promises to be one of the most dramatic episodes of the season.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test
episodes.overview: In the invention test, the winner of the mystery box challenge will get to decide on the pantry items, the cuisine and the cook time for every contestant.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Janice Wong's Cassis Plum
episodes.overview: The pressure test has been set by guest chef Janice Wong from 2am Dessert Bar in Singapore.The contestants have two hours and 15 minutes to recreate her intricate dessert, the cassis plum.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Batter
episodes.overview: In a battle for immunity, the contestants have 30 minutes to create a dish that showcases batter. However, the pantry and garden are off limits, so they must work with the staple ingredients...

episodes.name: Team Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants will take part in a barbecue battle in the MasterChef Australia garden for the team challenge. Special guest, Andy Groneman, will be there to guide them.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Rick Stein
episodes.overview: The judges reveal that the challenge is all about fish, and who better to help guide the contestants through the cook than much-loved chef Rick Stein, the 'Codfather' himself.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: The top eight contestants will take a trip down memory lane as they discover that this week's mystery box challenge is one they have faced before.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: In what promises to be one of the toughest pressure tests yet seen in the MasterChef Australia kitchen, the bottom four contestants from the invention test must cook off to survive in the competition.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: In an immunity challenge like no other, the two contestants will cook off against two professional chefs in the second round. Do the home cooks have what it takes to out-cook the professionals?

episodes.name: Off-site Challenge: Circa, The Prince
episodes.overview: In the off-site team challenge, the judges reveal the contestants will be preparing a seven-course degustation menu for 40 diners at Circa: The Prince.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Time Auction
episodes.overview: The contestants facing elimination will take part in a time auction. Each contestant begins with 100 minutes to bid for items in three categories. The more they spend the less time they have to cook.

episodes.name: Marco Pierre White Team Challenge
episodes.overview: As promised, Marco Pierre White has returned to see how far the contestants have come and to push them to step up going into finals week.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Cook-along
episodes.overview: With no recipe and no clock, three contestants must cook along with Marco Pierre White. He will cook a classic dish and they must cook at the same time and the same pace.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The best performing contestants from Marco Pierre White's service challenge have the chance to cook for immunity. It is the last immunity pin up for grabs before finals week.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: French Restaurants
episodes.overview: This episodes French challenge splits the contestants into two teams and will be responsible for every aspect of the restaurant: planning the menu, creating dishes with no recipes and much more.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Childhood Memories
episodes.overview: The judges reveal that for the elimination challenge, the contestants need to draw on childhood memories as an inspiration for their dish.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: It's finals week in the kitchen, the top five contestants enter the kitchen to face the last mystery box challenge.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The three contestants from the invention test will cook off in a pressure test, at the end of which, one more contestant will be going home.

episodes.name: No Rules Challenge
episodes.overview: In this challenge the contestants can choose their own cuisine and whether it's sweet or savoury, however they must decide on the cooking time together.

episodes.name: Service Challenge: The Press Club
episodes.overview: The judges reveal to the contestants that they will be running service in The Press Club, and will be cooking a four-course meal for 35 of the finest chefs and restaurateurs in the country.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: While one contestant has safely made it through to the semi-final, the remaining three are fighting it out to stay in the competition in a pressure test that will stretch them to their limits.

episodes.name: Grand Final Part 1
episodes.overview: The stakes are high as the three remaining contestants fight it out for the two places in the finale. One contestant will cook their last dish in the MasterChef Australia kitchen.

episodes.name: Grand Final Part 2
episodes.overview: Tune in as the winner of MasterChef Australia 2015 will be crowned. The finalists are competing for a $250,000 prize, a monthly column in Australia's leading premium food magazine 'Delicious' + more!

episodes.name: Premiere
episodes.overview: MasterChef Australia returns with the best group of home cooks the competition has ever seen. In the first of three judges' auditions, our amateur cooks are given one hour to cook their best dish.

episodes.name: 2nd Judges' Auditions
episodes.overview: In the second judges' auditions our amateur cooks are given one hour to cook their best dish. To receive an apron, the contestants must receive a yes from all three judges.

episodes.name: Final Round Judges' Auditions
episodes.overview: With the Final Round of the Judge's Audition comes the First Pressure Test, which involves a Shannon Bennett Chocolate Bar.

episodes.name: First Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: 2015's Masterchef, Billie McKay, knows exactly what this crop of aspirants are going through. Do you reckon she'll go easy on them when she picks the ingredients of the First Mystery Box?

episodes.name: First Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: In the first elimination challenge, three contestants choose a cloche containing a single ingredient to be used in a dish for the judges. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be going home.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Marco Pierre White
episodes.overview: The hopeful chefs suit up and show up for Marco Pierre White Week. With 75 minutes ticking away, they use the ingredients from Marco's mystery box of ingredients.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Marco Pierre White's John Dory
episodes.overview: It takes 20 ovens, miles of stainless steel, an arsenal of appliances and knives that chop, cut, slice and dice, to discover the best amateur chef in Australia. Tasks include mystery boxes, celebrity chef challenges, masterclasses and off-site challenges. The usual elimination format applies. MasterChef experts are George Calombaris, Gary Mehigan and Matt Preston.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Jake Kellie
episodes.overview: The top three contestants from the invention test must make a filled pasta with a matching sauce. The winner will then enter a cook off for immunity against guest chef, Jake Kellie.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Pub Lunch
episodes.overview: This challenge is all about the pub lunch. The contestants are split into two teams and must cook three courses for 70 people with Marco Pierre White running the pass.

episodes.name: Pressure Test & Masterclass
episodes.overview: The contestants from the losing pub lunch challenge team must correctly name an ingredient to avoid the elimination cook-off challenge, as the contestant with the least impressive dish will go home.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Viewers
episodes.overview: This mystery box challenge has been chosen by the viewers. Contestants have 75 minutes to create a dish using at least one ingredient chosen by the viewers.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The three contestants with the least impressive dishes from last nights the invention test face off in the pressure test. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be going home.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Popcorn
episodes.overview: The three best performers in the invention test must create a dish using popcorn as the core ingredient. The winner will then need to out-cook the professional guest chef for immunity.

episodes.name: Service Challenge
episodes.overview: In this service challenge, the contestants are split into two teams. Each team must cook a three-course meal for 30 people replicating dishes from two celebrated Melbourne restaurants.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: No Cooking
episodes.overview: The losing team from the service challenge now faces elimination as the contestants create a dish without any cooking. The bottom three will then cook-off to avoid elimination from the competition.

episodes.name: Mystery Box: Nigella Lawson
episodes.overview: It's Nigella Lawson Week. Contestants have 75 minutes to create a delicious dish based on Nigella's divine indulgences. The top three will have a chance at immunity while the bottom three face elimination.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Nigella Lawson's Three-Course Meal
episodes.overview: The bottom three from Nigella's invention test face elimination in what might be the toughest pressure test ever, as contestants have just one hour to recreate Nigella's three-course meal.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Midnight Snack
episodes.overview: Matt Preston and Nigella Lawson arrive at the contestant house in the middle of the night as the three best from Nigella's invention test are asked to create a midnight snack for a chance at immunity.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Fete
episodes.overview: Split into three teams, each team must prepare one savoury dish and two sweet dishes to sell at a fete held in honour of Nigella Lawson with all proceeds donated to the Royal Children's Hospital.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Name That Cake & MasterClass 2
episodes.overview: The losing fete challenge team now face elimination. Contestants must correctly name cakes, fail to do so and they will need to impress the judges with a cake of their own to stay in the competition.

episodes.name: Mystery Box
episodes.overview: The contestants have 60 minutes to create a dish using the ingredients in the mystery box. The winner will cook off for a chance at immunity and the bottom three will face the elimination pressure test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Jason Atherton's Quail Afternoon Tea Dish
episodes.overview: The bottom three from the invention test now face the elimination pressure test. Contestants have just over 3 hours to recreate UK chef Jason Atherton's quail afternoon tea dish to avoid elimination.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: With immunity up for grabs, contestants will work in pairs to create a savoury & sweet jaffle in 45 minutes. The winning pair will then need to out cook professional chefs to secure an immunity pin.

episodes.name: Off-site Challenge: Hellenic Republic
episodes.overview: Today's off-site challenge will take place at George Calombaris' Hellenic Republic restaurant. Split into two teams, each team must prepare a three course feast for 120 guests to avoid elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Blind Taste Test
episodes.overview: The losing Greek feast challenge team now face elimination. Contestants who fail the Round 1 blind taste test must then impress the judges with a dish using the ingredient they did not correctly name.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test
episodes.overview: The Queen of the Australian kitchen, Maggie Beer returns! The invention test winner will have the advantage going into the mystery box challenge when contestants have an hour to impress the judges.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Anna Polyviou's Mess
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the mystery box challenge face off in the elimination pressure test. Contestants have just three hours to recreate & 15 minutes to plate up Anna Polyviou's mess.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The three best performers from Maggie Beer's mystery box are now vying for immunity. The contestant who produces the best éclair in round one will then cook off against a professional chef.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Chinese New Year
episodes.overview: Today's off-site team challenge marks the celebration of Chinese New Year joined by guest mentor, Kylie Kwong. Each team must prepare two set-price Asian street food dishes & sell them to the public.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The losing team from the Chinese New Year challenge must now cook a dish determined by lucky dip. With 75 minutes on the clock, the contestant with the least impressive dish will be eliminated.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Luke Nguyen & Invention Test
episodes.overview: Today's mystery box challenge has been set by guest chef Luke Nguyen, as contestants have 60 minutes to make an impressive dish. The winner will then gain the advantage going into the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Ross Lusted
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the invention test face off in the elimination pressure test. Contestants have just two hours to recreate two of guest chef Ross Lusted's signature dishes.

episodes.name: Top 12
episodes.overview: The judges reveal to the top 12 contestants that today there are some special guests joining them in the MasterChef Australia kitchen.

episodes.name: Team Challenge
episodes.overview: Guest chef Curtis Stone joins today's off-site team challenge. Each team must prepare a six-course degustation menu for 50 guests in only two and half hours to avoid the elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The losing team from the Curtis Stone challenge now face elimination. Who will be leaving the MasterChef Australia kitchen?

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Ugly Ingredients & Invention Test: Relay
episodes.overview: Today's mystery box challenge contains eight of the ugliest ingredients ever seen. The contestants must impress the judges by creating a beautiful & delicious dish in only 60 minutes.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Flynn McGarry
episodes.overview: The losing team from the invention test relay challenge now face off in the pressure test. Contestants must recreate guest chef Flynn McGarry's signature dish to avoid elimination.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Victor Liong
episodes.overview: The four contestants who impressed in the relay invention test cook for immunity. Does the winner of the first round have what it takes to out-cook guest chef Victor Liong from Lee Ho Fook?

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Gourmet Cinema
episodes.overview: In today's gourmet cinema team challenge, the judges reveal that the contestants must cater for 165 cinema goers at a very special cinema event - the screening of MasterChef Australia's Greatest Hits.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The losing team from the gourmet cinema challenge are now cooking to save themselves from elimination. If they survive, they will make it into the top 10.

episodes.name: Heston Week
episodes.overview: Heston Week. Heston Blumenthal returns to MasterChef Australia in the biggest week ever. In a world first, the top 10 contestants open four Heston inspired & supervised MasterChef Australia pop-ups in four days.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Brighton Beach Ice Cream Stands
episodes.overview: Heston Week. For one day only, Melbourne's iconic Brighton Beach bathing boxes become ice cream stands selling Heston-inspired ice creams & ice blocks. The least impressive team will face elimination.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Three-Course Dessert Spread
episodes.overview: Heston Week. Tonight's challenge, Heston inspires the contestants to create a three-course dessert spread using only the food of the Gods: chocolate. The least impressive team will face the elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Recipes from the Past
episodes.overview: Heston Week. Heston's restaurants are all about taking recipes from the past & giving them a modern twist. Four contestants must prepare a single course inspired by recipes from the past to avoid elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge & MasterClass 3
episodes.overview: Masterclass. The seven contestants who created the least impressive dishes during the pop-ups now face off to stay in the competition in the final Heston-inspired challenge. Plus, a special Heston Masterclass.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test
episodes.overview: The judges reveal that this week will be the toughest ever! In today's invention test contestants must choose between three of the hardest invention test dishes ever from previous seasons.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The three contestants with the least impressive dishes from last night's invention test face off in the pressure test. At the end of the cook, one of these contestants will be going home.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The three best performers in the invention test must now impress the judges in Round One for a chance to cook off against a professional chef and gain immunity.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Australian Produce
episodes.overview: The remaining eight contestants are split into teams of two to cook a two-course meal inspired by quality Australian produce for 80 diners. The two least impressive teams will face elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The four members of the losing teams from the service challenge now face elimination. With so much at stake, which contestant will fail to impress the judges and be sent home from the competition?

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: San Francisco Produce & Invention Test
episodes.overview: California Week. The MasterChef Australia competition travels to California for the week. With just a map in hand the contestants must track down today's mystery box ingredients from local San Francisco produce shops.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Dominque Crenn's Signature Dishes
episodes.overview: California Week. Contestants must work in teams to recreate two of Dominque Creen's signature dishes. Dominque is a Michelin-starred chef & was recently voted the World's Best Female Chef.

episodes.name: Francis Ford Coppola's Inglenook Estate
episodes.overview: California Week. Today four of the most impressive contestants are cooking for a guaranteed place in finals week at Francis Ford Coppola's Inglenook Estate in the Napa Valley.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Santa Monica Pier Food Trucks
episodes.overview: California Week. Today the contestants are split into teams to run their very own food trucks at the world famous Santa Monica Pier. There is plenty at stake with the winning team guaranteed a place in finals week.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge & MasterClass 4
episodes.overview: Masterclass. The losing team from the Food Truck Challenge now face elimination. Under the mentorship of Curtis Stone, they must cook a dish that symbolises what they're going to do once the competition is over.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Hottest Ingredients & Invention Test
episodes.overview: Finals Week. The top six contestants now face a mystery box challenge containing some of the hottest ingredients being used in the world right now. The winner will gain the advantage going into the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Christy Tania
episodes.overview: Finals Week. The bottom three contestants from the invention test now face the elimination pressure test set by pastry chef & dessert specialist, Christy Tania.

episodes.name: Service Challenge: Lake House
episodes.overview: Finals Week. The Top Five contestants must cook five dishes from the menu of the Lake House in Daylesford under the guidance of legendary chef & owner, Alla Wolf-Tasker.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Audition Ingredients
episodes.overview: Finals Week. The bottom 3 contestants from the Lake House challenge now face elimination & must impress the judges with a dish produced from the ingredients that they each cooked with to get into the competition.

episodes.name: MasterClass 5
episodes.overview: Masterclass. The final MasterClass of 2016 sees the return of the eliminated contestants. The shoe's on the other foot for George, Gary & Shannon who must cook a dish from ingredients from a special mystery box.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test: Quarter Final
episodes.overview: Grand Final Week. In today's Quarter Final mystery box challenge & invention test, contestants cook off for a place in the Semi Final using ingredients chosen by their loved ones.

episodes.name: Service Challenge: Semi Final
episodes.overview: Grand Final Week. The final three contestants vie for a place in the Grand Finale in tonight's service challenge. Each contestant must prepare a main and a dessert for 20 guests plus the three judges.

episodes.name: MasterChef 2016 Grand Finale
episodes.overview: Grand Finale. Who will be crowned the winner of MasterChef Australia 2016? The finalists are competing for a $250,000 cash prize & a column in Australia's leading premium food magazine, Delicious.

episodes.name: Auditions Part 1
episodes.overview: The heat is on. A fresh group of home cooks from around the country will eagerly tackle challenges that will see one of them take home the title and $250,000.

episodes.name: Auditions Part 2
episodes.overview: After a record-breaking first-round cook that saw an extraordinary 20 aprons handed out, only four aprons remain. Who will have what it takes to impress the judges?

episodes.name: Auditions Part 3
episodes.overview: In the third and final round of the judge's auditions, six contestants are vying for the final apron, which will secure them a place in the top 24.

episodes.name: Mystery Box: Elena Duggan
episodes.overview: Top 24 Mystery Box Challenge: Elena Duggan The top 24 contestants enter the kitchen for their first mystery box challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Hidden Pairs
episodes.overview: Hidden Pairs Elimination Challenge Bottom 4 cooking of in the mystery pairs elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Judges' Mystery Box Challenge and Invention Test
episodes.overview: Each judge has placed three of their favourite ingredients into the mystery box and contestants will have 75 minutes to create a remarkable dish for a chance at immunity.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Gary Mehigan's Roast Chicken, Peas and Potatoes
episodes.overview: The three contestants with the least impressive dishes from the invention test face off in the pressure test. To survive they must keep up with Gary Mehigan as he prepares his classic roast chicken.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Jarrod Di Blasi
episodes.overview: The top three contestants from the invention test now compete in creating a family meal for four in half-an-hour. The winner will then take on a professional chef for a chance at immunity.

episodes.name: 400 Gradi Team Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants gather at Gradi, one of Melbourne's leading Italian restaurants before being split into two teams who must prepare four dishes for 250 hungry diners to avoid the elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Potato & Masterclass
episodes.overview: The losing team from the Italian service challenge face elimination. Who will be the next to leave the competition? Plus, don't miss the first MasterClass of 2017 led by judges Gary, George and Matt.

episodes.name: Mystery Box: Ben Shewry
episodes.overview: Contestants have 75 minutes to create a dish using ingredients from the mystery box with the winner gaining the advantage in the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Andy Bowdy's Rita cake
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the invention test now face a pressure test to recreate Andy Bowdy's Rita cake to avoid elimination. Who will be the next to leave the competition?

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Waffle Iron
episodes.overview: The three best performers from the invention test are now vying for a chance at immunity. Does the amateur cook have what it takes to out-cook the professional?

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Relay
episodes.overview: The contestants are split into teams of four in a relay challenge as each member has 15 minutes to cook and only 45 seconds to hand over to the next cook in the relay.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Time Auction
episodes.overview: The losing team from the relay challenge now face elimination and the contestants have 90 minutes which they can use to buy ingredients. Who will be the next to leave the competition?

episodes.name: Mystery Box: Delicious Dessert
episodes.overview: Contestants have 90 minutes to create a delicious dessert from the mystery box ingredients. However, only five dishes will be tasted and only three will move on to the immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Christy Tania's Ice Cream Float
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the invention test now face off in the pressure test elimination, and have to recreate an ice cream float with a helium-filled toffee ballon.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The three best-performing contestants from the invention test compete for immunity. Each contestant has 90 minutes to create a dessert while the professional chefs will only have 75 minutes.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Edible Art Installation
episodes.overview: Contestants will be working in teams to build an edible art installation in a specially constructed greenhouse. With just 8 hours to impress the judges which team will be safe from elimination?

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Blind Taste Test
episodes.overview: The losing team from the greenhouse challenge now face elimination. The first three to fail the blindfold taste test will have 75 minutes to prepare an impressive dish to stay in the competition.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test
episodes.overview: Contestants have 75 minutes to create a delicious dish from the mystery box of traditional Thai ingredients to gain advantage in the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Josue Lopez's After the Eucalypt Fire
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the invention test now cook off in a three hour pressure test set by 2016's Chef of the Year. Who will impress and who has cooked their last dish in the competition?

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The three best performers in the invention test battle it out for the chance to cook for an immunity pin. Will the amateur contestant have what it takes to out-cook a professional?

episodes.name: Team Challenge: South Melbourne Market
episodes.overview: Each team must serve two dishes in one of four market-friendly ways at the famous South Melbourne Market. The two teams that make the least amount of money will face off in an elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Eight contestants now face elimination and must survive three rounds if they are to keep their food dream alive. Will one of the top contenders fail to impress the judges?

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Yotam Ottolenghi & Invention Test
episodes.overview: Master of Mediterranean cuisine, Yotam Ottolenghi's mystery box challenge gives contestants 75 minutes to create a delicious dish to gain an advantage going into the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Yotam's Mezze Feast
episodes.overview: The three contestants with the least impressive dishes from the invention test must cook off to avoid elimination in a pressure test set by the master of Mediterranean cuisine, Yotam Ottolenghi.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The three best performers in the invention test must first face off for a chance to cook against a professional chef for immunity. Does an amateur have what it takes to defeat a professional?

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Vegetarian Feast
episodes.overview: Split into two teams, each group must prepare a Yotam Ottolenghi-style vegetarian feast for a group of meat lovers. The team that serves the least impressive feast will be up for elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge & MasterClass
episodes.overview: The seven members of the losing team from the vegetarian feast challenge are facing elimination. Which favourite will be going home? Plus, a very special Yotam Ottolenghi MasterClass.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test: Curtis Stone
episodes.overview: Contestants have an hour to create a delicious dish from ingredients found in the Mystery Box set by international celebrity chef Curtis Stone.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Deniz Karaca's Passion for Caramel
episodes.overview: The bottom four contestants from the invention test must now cook off in the Pressure Test set by one of the world's top chocolatiers to avoid elimination. Who will be next to leave the competition?

episodes.name: Second Chance
episodes.overview: Twelve of the previously eliminated contestants now have a chance to cook their way back into the competition. Which one of the home cooks will secure themselves a second chance?

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Pop-Up Restaurant
episodes.overview: MasterChef Australia2016 runner-up Matt Sinclair is on hand to mentor contestants in a pop-up restaurant team challenge to create a three-course menu for 100 diners.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The six members of the losing team from the pop-up restaurant challenge enter the kitchen facing elimination. Who will be the next contestant to leave the competition?

episodes.name: Heston Blumenthal Road Trip
episodes.overview: It's Heston Blumenthal week. Heston takes the top 12 contestants on a road trip through regional Victoria; the first stop is the mighty Murray River in Swan Hill.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Earth
episodes.overview: Contestants split into pairs have 75 minutes to cook one main and one dessert that must incorporate the element of earth. The least impressive team will then need to cook off to avoid elimination.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Air
episodes.overview: The judges and Heston Blumenthal welcome the eight contestants to the Mildura salt pan. The contestants must cook dishes inspired by 'air' in teams of four.

episodes.name: Invention Test: Fire
episodes.overview: Contestants have 60 minutes to cook a savoury dish inspired by fire. The two least impressive dishes must then cook off to avoid the elimination challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge & MasterClass 3
episodes.overview: Contestants have 75 minutes to cook a delicious dish to avoid elimination. Later, Heston Blumenthal's MasterClass shows how to cook a tasty BBQ leg of Mallee lamb.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test
episodes.overview: Contestants have an hour to create a dish from the Mystery Box ingredients, with only three dishes to be tasted. The maker of the winning dish will receive an advantage in the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Paul Carmichael's Bajan Fish Fry
episodes.overview: Unwatched The contestants have three hours and 45 minutes to recreate Paul Carmichael's Bajan fish fry from Momofuku Seiobo. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be eliminated from the competition.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The three best performers from the invention test now compete for a chance at immunity. Will our amateur cook have what it takes to out-perform one of Australia's best chefs?

episodes.name: Team Challenge: Identical Plates
episodes.overview: Split into pairs, each team must make two plates of the same dish and they must be identical, but they will not be able to see or taste what their team mate is cooking.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The bottom four contestants from the team challenge now must cook off and produce a spectacular dish to stay alive in the competition.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: This program is about to get even bigger as the competition travels to the land of the cherry blossom, Japan. Contestants must explore Tokyo to find ingredients for the mystery box challenge.

episodes.name: Kappo-style Degustation Menu
episodes.overview: Each of the eight contestants will have to conceive, cook and deliver one course as part of an eight-course Kappo-style degustation for some of Tokyo's food elite.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The winning contestants from the invention test and the Kappo challenge now have a chance to fight it out for immunity in view of Mount Fuji at the Obuchi Tea Plantation.

episodes.name: Off-site Challenge: Shinjuku
episodes.overview: The judges welcome contestants to the heart of Shinjuku, where Tokyo comes alive at night. Contestants will be cooking at a local alleyway packed with street stalls to feed hundreds of hungry diners.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The losing team from the Yokocho street stall challenge must cook off to stay in the competition. Contestants must cook a dish that celebrates where they have come from and where they are going.

episodes.name: Japan Week Masterclass
episodes.overview: Japan week concludes at Tateyama Castle for a very special MasterClass with Michelin star sushi chef who walks the contestants through the simplicity and beauty of the perfect sushi.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test
episodes.overview: Contestants have an hour to create a dish from four mystery ingredients to gain advantage in the invention test. Later, contestants must recreate a classic dish and avoid facing elimination.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Kylie Millar
episodes.overview: The three least impressive contestants from the invention test cook off in a pressure test set by MasterChef alumni, Kylie Millar. Who has cooked their last dish in the kitchen?

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The three best invention test performers now face a special souffle immunity challenge. Can our amateur chef out-cook a professional and find themselves cooking in finals week?

episodes.name: Service Challenge: 50 Hungry Customers
episodes.overview: The judges reveal that each contestant will be in charge of either an entree, main or dessert to serve 50 hungry customers. The bottom three contestants will then be up for elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The three least impressive contestants from the service challenge must cook to stay in the competition and earn their place in finals week. Who will be the next to leave?

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test
episodes.overview: It's finals week. The top six contestants enter the kitchen to face a mystery box challenge to prove to the judges just how far they have come in the competition.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Shaun Quade's Pearl on the Ocean Floor
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the invention test now cook off in a pressure test to avoid elimination. Who will be the next to leave the competition?

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The top five contestants must create either a sweet or savoury dish and present seven plates of food for the judges as well as four of Australia’s top chefs to avoid elimination from the competition.

episodes.name: Service Challenge: Dinner by Heston
episodes.overview: The pressure is on as the top four contestants enter one of Melbourne's top restaurants, Dinner By Heston, for a service challenge. Who will be the first semifinalist?

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge & MasterClass 5
episodes.overview: Three contestants must create a dish worthy of a place in the semifinal. The final MasterClass of the season sees the tables turned on Gary, George and Shannon, who compete in a mystery box challenge. Later, Curtis Stone drops by to take part in an invention test relay.

episodes.name: Semi Final
episodes.overview: The stakes are high as the three remaining contestants fight it out for the two places in the finale and the chance of winning the coveted prize.

episodes.name: Grand Final
episodes.overview: Who will be crowned the winner of 2017? The finalists are competing for a $250,000 cash prize and a column in Australia's leading premium food magazine, Delicious.

episodes.name: Auditions Part 1
episodes.overview: The amateur cooks are given one hour to recreate their signature dish for the first of the two judges' auditions. The judges introduce the nine past winners of the program, who are there to cheer them on.

episodes.name: Auditions Part 2
episodes.overview: After handing out 18 aprons on the first day of cooking, the judges are looking for six more cooks to round out the top 24. The cooks who were given a second chance will battle it out in a challenge.

episodes.name: Individual Hospitality Cooking Challenge
episodes.overview: Our 2018 cooks enter the MasterChef kitchen for their first challenge as the top 24. The contestants need to imagine they are hosting the judges at their house for a meal, cooking anything they want.

episodes.name: Home Fridge Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: In the first elimination challenge of the season, three contestants fight to stay in the competition. They are given 75 minutes to cook, using only the ingredients contained in their fridges from home.

episodes.name: Eclectic Mystery Box Challenge & Perception Invention Test
episodes.overview: The 23 cooks enter the kitchen for the first mystery box challenge of the season. This time, the rules are changing: the winner of the mystery box will get a game-changing advantage.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Maggie Beer
episodes.overview: The three contestants with the least impressive dishes from the invention test face-off in the pressure test. Queen of the kitchen Maggie Beer enters with the dish to be recreated.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Shui Ishizaki
episodes.overview: The winner of the mystery box challenge and the three best-performing cooks from the invention test will compete for immunity, with Shannon Bennett back in the kitchen to guide and mentor the contestants.

episodes.name: Team Challenge: MCG
episodes.overview: The contestants find themselves on the turf of the iconic MCG for the first team challenge. Split into two teams, each must cook delicious and nutritious food for 50 diners using a different protein.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Source of Inspiration
episodes.overview: The losing team from the MCG service challenge must face-off in this elimination challenge. The contestants must cook something inspired by the dish that made them fall in love with food.

episodes.name: Nigella's Mystery Box & Invention Test
episodes.overview: Culinary goddess Nigella Lawson arrives in the kitchen for a week of challenges and surprises. The lid is lifted on Nigella's mystery box to reveal some of her favourite ingredients.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Nigella Lawson
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the previous invention test will face off in this episode's pressure test. The contestants have 75 minutes to complete four of Nigella Lawson's favourite chocolate dishes.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Alanna Sapwell
episodes.overview: The winning contestant from the mystery box challenge joins the top three contestants from the invention test in this episode's two round immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Battle Of The Brunch
episodes.overview: In a team service challenge, it will be a battle of the brunches, as in two groups of 10, they take over two cafes. Contestants will have real customers, with real orders and real dockets.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge & Nigella's Masterclass
episodes.overview: The contestants in the losing team are in the kitchen for what will be the last time for one of them. Plus, the first Masterclass of the season with Nigella Lawson.

episodes.name: Gordon Ramsay's Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test
episodes.overview: In one of the biggest surprises of the season so far, and in a program first, Gordon Ramsay enters the kitchen for a mystery box challenge.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Gordon Ramsay
episodes.overview: With Gordon Week off to a flying start, the bottom three contestants in the invention test roll up to the kitchen ready to cook for their place in the competition with a pressure test.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - 3 vs 3
episodes.overview: Our mystery box winner and the top two dishes from the invention test will have the chance to cook for immunity with Gordon Ramsay as their mentor.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Three-course meal
episodes.overview: The contestants enter the kitchen only to find Gordon Ramsay, who is already yelling at them to hurry up. Divided into two teams, they prepare a three-course meal for 50 diners.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Gordon's Challenge
episodes.overview: It's the last day of Gordon week. The team who lost the service challenge will have to cook for their lives. The contestants had to recreate a three-Michelin star chicken dish from Restaurant Gordon Ramsay by chef Matt Abé in the two-and a-half hour Pressure Test

episodes.name: 20/20 Mystery Box Challenge & Honey Invention Test
episodes.overview: Contestants are shopping for their own mystery box ingredients with only $20 and 20 minutes. Maker of the best dish goes through to the immunity challenge, followed by the winners of the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Darren Purchese
episodes.overview: The losing team from yesterday's invention test are in the kitchen, ready to fight for their place in the competition.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Jacqui Challinor
episodes.overview: The winner of Sunday night's mystery box, along with the members of the winning team in the invention test relay will compete for a coveted immunity pin.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - From Memory
episodes.overview: The judges surprise the contestants by announcing that this episode, a few of them will be journeying to the wide blue yonder.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Curtis Stone
episodes.overview: The eight contestants who lost the previous challenge are cooking in this episode's elimination, with Curtis Stone to keep them company.

episodes.name: South Australia Mystery Box Challenge & Night Market Team Challenge
episodes.overview: It's the beginning of South Australia Week for the contestants, where they will be cooking with some of the best ingredients South Australia has to offer.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - D'Arenberg Cube
episodes.overview: The contestants find themselves at the incredible D'Arenberg Cube restaurant in the heart of McLaren Vale wine country, with the bottom two teams from the night market challenge facing elimination.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Mt Lofty House
episodes.overview: This immunity challenge takes place at the stunning Mt Lofty House in the Adelaide Hills. Does our contestant have what it takes to outscore the chef and win immunity?

episodes.name: Table Grapes Team Challenge - Barossa Valley
episodes.overview: The team challenge will take place in the Barossa Valley. Divided into two teams, contestants will be given two hours to prepare an entree, main and dessert with each course celebrating table grapes.

episodes.name: Maggie Beer's Elimination Challenge & Poh and Callum's Masterclass
episodes.overview: For the elimination challenge, the contestants go to Maggie Beer's Eatery in the Barossa Valley. Plus, a masterclass takes place at the Adelaide Markets.

episodes.name: Mystery Bread Box Challenge & Spaghetti Bolognese Reinvention Test
episodes.overview: The contestants arrive back at the kitchen after a week of adventure in South Australia. There is a lot at stake, knowing that the top 10 is just around the corner.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Alla Wolf-Tasker
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the invention test are facing elimination.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Andy Harmer
episodes.overview: The winner of the mystery box and the top three from the invention test have the chance to cook for immunity.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Three-course fire challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants find themselves in the Dandenong Ranges where a fiery team challenge awaits them. To cook a three-course meal, all they have to use is fire.

episodes.name: World Cuisine Elimination Challenge & Second Chance Cook-Off
episodes.overview: The losing team from the previous challenge arrive at the kitchen for what will be the last time for one of them.

episodes.name: Adriano Zumbo’s Mystery Box Challenge & Team Invention Test – Sweet Week
episodes.overview: The judges reveal this is Sweet Week. To kick off the week, they introduce the master of sweets, Adriano Zumbo, who has selected the mystery box ingredients and will reveal the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Katherine Sabbath
episodes.overview: Continuing Sweet Week, the judges are joined by social media cake superstar Katherine Sabbath. The bottom two teams from the previous invention test will face off in a pressure test.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Alice Wright
episodes.overview: Our two Sweet Week mystery box winners and the winning team from Zumbo’s invention test compete for immunity over two rounds

episodes.name: Team Service Challenge – Tonka & Coda
episodes.overview: George pays a surprise visit to the Masterchef contestant house with a special guest. Together, they reveal the challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Kirsten Tibballs
episodes.overview: The losing team from the previous challenge will fight for their place in the competition.

episodes.name: The Everything Mystery Box & Dish for a King
episodes.overview: For the mystery box challenge the contestants find a big surprise among their ingredients. Later, the invention test is a chance for the contestants to prove they deserve to be in the top 10.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Saransh Goila
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the invention test face elimination in a pressure test.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Ashley Davis
episodes.overview: The mystery box winner and the top three contestants from the invention test compete for immunity.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Canapes for the Royal Reception
episodes.overview: The contestants receive a surprise message in the MasterChef house which informs them of their next group challenge and where they'll be travelling to.

guest_stars.name: King Charles III of the United Kingdom
guest_stars.original_name: King Charles III of the United Kingdom

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Picture Perfect
episodes.overview: Continuing their adventure, the contestants arrive at their next destination. The two losing teams from the previous challenge face elimination in this challenge.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge - Surprise Ingredient & Invention Test: Oil, Salt and Pepper
episodes.overview: This week the judges have a surprise - it's survival week and the contestants will be cooking for their lives every day. By the end of the week one of them will win the most powerful advantage.

episodes.name: Re-Invention Test - Retro TV Dinners
episodes.overview: As survival week continues, the contestants are shocked to discover that another challenge may lead to elimination. Tonight, they have to turn a tray of terror in to a modern masterpiece.

episodes.name: Time or Ingredients
episodes.overview: The contestants remaining in survival week will learn all about making decisions under pressure as they decide what is of more value to them: time or ingredients.

episodes.name: Off-Site Challenge - Panama Dining Room
episodes.overview: The challenge is off site at Panama Dining Room, in Melbourne's inner-city suburb of Fitzroy. The contestants will be cooking a main course and dessert for 25 people each.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Peter Gilmore's Snow Egg & Masterclass
episodes.overview: This is no ordinary elimination, but a pressure test with an iconic dish. How will the contestants cope with this massive challenge? Plus, join us for a masterclass

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge - Loved Ones & Invention Test - Vue de Monde
episodes.overview: Our 7 remaining contestants are in the MasterChef kitchen ready to fight for their place with a big surprise awaiting them. What will the contestants be challenged with for tonight's invention test?

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Joe Grbac
episodes.overview: The bottom three contestants from the invention test face elimination. Which of our contestants will be able to save their place in the competition with a pressure test like no other?

episodes.name: Fast-Track to Finals Week - Matt or Reynold?
episodes.overview: The winner of the mystery box and of the invention test will face off in round one, vying for the chance to cook off against a professional cook in round two to get fast tracked to Finals Week.

episodes.name: Off-Site Challenge - Second Bite at Luminare
