episodes.overview: This episode is all about raising money for Second Bite, a charity that the program supports. The contestants will cook using only ingredients donated by the charity, cooking a six-course degustation.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Taste Test in Three Rounds & Curtis Stone's MasterClass
episodes.overview: This is the final elimination before Finals Week, and will determine the top five for 2018. It's an elimination over three rounds. Plus, a MasterClass with Curtis Stone.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge - Past Seasons & Invention Test - No Rules
episodes.overview: Today marks the first day of Finals Week for 2018. Each contestant will cook with one of five mystery boxes from a past season - who will be make it through to the next challenge?

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Ashley Palmer-Watts
episodes.overview: It’s the first pressure test of finals week and the bottom three contestants from the previous invention test line up for what will be the last time in the MasterChef kitchen for one of them.

episodes.name: Two-Round Cook-Off - Three Seasons
episodes.overview: We are down to the top four in the competition and they will compete for a massive advantage. Just days from the grand finale, this advantage will be a game changer.

episodes.name: Service Challenge - Icebergs
episodes.overview: The contestants arrive in Sydney at the iconic Icebergs restaurant in Bondi. They are competing for a place in the semifinal and need to be inspired by the Italian menu at Icebergs.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Three-Course Meal for Four Top Chefs & MasterClass
episodes.overview: The elimination challenge will determine who will go into the semifinal. The bottom three contestants will fight it out for their place in the competition. Plus, a final MasterClass of the season.

episodes.name: Semi-Finals - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: It is the semifinal of 2018. Our top three contestants are told that they will be cooking for some very special guests.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: It’s the grand finale of 2018 and our top 24 has been whittled down to two home cooks battling it out in one final day in the kitchen.

episodes.name: Auditions: Day 1
episodes.overview: Each hopeful cook has 60 minutes to produce their dish. If the judges like the dish, they're through to the next stage. If not, sadly, they're heading home.

episodes.name: Auditions: Day 2
episodes.overview: It's day two of auditions and 13 contestants return for a second chance to show the judges they deserve to be in the top 24. With 18 aprons given away yesterday, just six aprons are up for grabs.

episodes.name: Desert Island Dish
episodes.overview: The pantry is open, there's 75 minutes on the clock, and the contestants are asked to cook the dish they'd cook every day for the rest of their lives if they found themselves on a desert island.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Curtis Stone
episodes.overview: It's the end of the first week in the kitchen and the winners from the previous challenge will cook for an immunity pin. But it won't be easy: they'll be cooking against chef Curtis Stone.

episodes.name: Special Ingredient Mystery Box & Black Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: It's mystery box time and our cooks must create a delicious dish using at least one of the elected ingredients. Next up is the black mystery box, but this time, whoever cooks the worst dish is going home.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Darren Purchese
episodes.overview: Those that failed to impress in the previous episode are facing the dreaded pressure test. Our cooks are charged with recreating a Darren Purchese dessert, and whoever doesn't impress the judges will be going home.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Max Sharrad
episodes.overview: The winners of the mystery box and invention test face the immunity challenge. History is made when the judges choose who will cook against Young Chef of the Year, Max Sharrad.

episodes.name: Off-Site Team Challenge - Briagolong Drought Feast
episodes.overview: Contestants cook outside of the kitchen for the first time. Their challenge is to create a feast for volunteers, truckies, farmers and their families impacted by drought in Briagolong.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Choices! & Masterclass 1
episodes.overview: Before each cook sits their favourite and least favourite ingredients. Round one: cook with either. But those that produce the bottom four dishes face round two with their remaining ingredient. Followed by a Masterclass with Billie, Poh and Matt

episodes.name: Nigella's Mystery Box Challenge & Team Relay Invention Test
episodes.overview: It's Nigella Week. MasterChef favourite Nigella Lawson sets the mystery box ingredients. Whoever cooks the best dish heads into immunity, but the rest must compete in a relay invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Nigella's Roast Chicken
episodes.overview: It's pressure test time for the losing team from the previous challenge. The contestants have 90 minutes to cook Nigella's infamous roast chicken with two sides and gravy. Who will fail to impress and be sent home?

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Coskun Uysal
episodes.overview: Nigella week continues, and the four best cooks from her Mystery Box challenge must cook a dish that celebrates custard. The top contestant will compete against Coskun Uysal, of renowned Tulum restaurant.

episodes.name: Off-Site Team Challenge - State Library of Victoria with Nigella
episodes.overview: Nigella and contestants are given historical recipes at the State Library of Victoria to inspire a three-course meal. The team who create the least impressive menu will head into the next elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Condiments & Masterclass 2 with Nigella
episodes.overview: The bottom team from the previous challenge are presented with an array of condiments they must identify correctly. The first five to guess incorrectly head into an elimination cook. Plus, a Masterclass with Nigella.

episodes.name: Rick Stein's Mystery Box Challenge & Fish and Potatoes Invention Test
episodes.overview: It's Legends Week and our cooks have to create a dish using Rick Stein's Mystery Box. Later, a fish and potatoes themed Invention Test determines who will face the Immunity Challenge and Pressure Test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Clare Smyth's Dessert
episodes.overview: This episode's Pressure Test has contestants recreating a dessert from culinary legend Clare Smyth. During four hours of preparation time, there are tears and even a dish that collapses before the judges' eyes.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Donovan Cooke
episodes.overview: Matt Sinclair mentors the Immunity cook which uses only equipment from a typical office kitchen. Best dish enters Round 2, where they will compete against culinary legend Donovan Cooke.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Street Food for 360!
episodes.overview: Joined by Yotam Ottolenghi, our contestants are cooking street food for 360 people. Each team must hero a different cuisine, and the least impressive team will be sent into the next elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Deli Challenge with Yotam Ottolenghi
episodes.overview: Legends week continues as Yotam Ottolenghi hosts a deli item challenge. The first three contestants to incorrectly name a deli item must cook to stay in the competition. Who will be heading home?

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test - Secret's Week
episodes.overview: It's Secrets Week, and, after a quick workshop with Din Tai Fung's Edward Yulianto, our cooks must create a tasty dumpling dish and later invent a dish that incorporates a secret. Shh.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Paella by Leno Lattarulo
episodes.overview: Three contestants face a pressure test and will cook a paella based on an award-winning dish by Leno Lattarulo from Melbourne's Simply Spanish. Simple, right? Wrong. It is Secrets Week, after all.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Sauce, Secrets and Citrus
episodes.overview: These immunity rounds involve sauce, secrets and citrus. A contestant will face off against an established chef that will be kept secret from everyone, including the judges, until the very end.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Secret Weapons
episodes.overview: Each team is allocated a 'secret weapon' and must create a four-course Italian meal for 40 diners. Whichever team serves the least impressive meal will go into the next pressure test.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Blindfold Taste Test & One Last Secret
episodes.overview: Secrets Week closes with the previous episode's losing team facing a blindfolded taste test. The first five to guess incorrectly have a 60-minute open pantry cook, but one last secret will ruffle some feathers.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test - Queensland
episodes.overview: This episode's mystery box challenge has contestants creating dishes using Queensland's finest ingredients. The judges will taste the five most appealing dishes and the winner will head into an immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - Shannon Kellam
episodes.overview: Contestants must re-create one of Shannon Kellam's signature dishes, but without a recipe. The contestant who re-creates the dish least like Shannon's will be going home.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Ginger & Ben Williamson
episodes.overview: In round one, contestants must prepare a sweet or savoury dish with one of Queensland's finest ingredients - ginger. The winner will cook off against chef Ben Williamson for an immunity pin.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - BBQ For 150 Noosa Locals
episodes.overview: The Queensland trip continues and the teams must cook a barbecue feast to serve 150 Noosa locals. The team that serves the least impressive feast will go into the next elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Skills Test/ Seafood Platter Challenge & Masterclass with Ash Martin
episodes.overview: In this episode's elimination, contestants undergo a skills test followed by a seafood platter challenge including raw, fried and steamed elements. MasterClass with judges and Homage restaurant's Ash Martin.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test - The Dreaded Everything Box
episodes.overview: It is the dreaded Everything Box, where contestants must use every one of the eight ingredients. They will have to be extra creative if they want to win a place in the next immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Pressure Test – The Surprise Twist!
episodes.overview: Three contestants will face the chopping block in an elimination challenge with a surprise twist.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge – Letters from home & Jessie McTavish
episodes.overview: Contestants awake with letters from home containing special instructions for round one of the immunity cook. The winner will cook off against chef Jessie McTavish from North Bondi Fish.

episodes.name: Team Challenge – A Picnic At Hanging Rock with Maggie Beer
episodes.overview: Contestants find themselves in the Macedon Ranges for this team challenge: a picnic at Hanging Rock. What will be a surprise is who is the guest chef - none other than the beloved Maggie Beer.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge – with Maggie Beer
episodes.overview: Maggie Beer is back for the elimination challenge which will take place over two rounds. In round one, the contestants must celebrate herbs from the garden. In round two, they must feature spices.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test with Heston Blumenthal – Sweet Week
episodes.overview: Kicking off Sweet Week, molecular master Heston Blumenthal enters the kitchen with a mystery box for the contestants.

episodes.name: Pressure Test – Kate Reid
episodes.overview: In a surprise twist, our bottom three contestants from the cereal invention test have been thrown straight into a pressure test. Aprons on: it's time to cook a unique creation by Kate Reid.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Ice Cream Challenge & Alice Wright
episodes.overview: Sweet Week continues with an immunity ice cream challenge. In round two, the best cook will go up against chef Alice Wright.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Identical!
episodes.overview: The team challenge requires contestants to create a delicious, sweet dish that is identical in look, texture and flavour to their teammate's dish. Communication is key.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge – The Dessert With No Sugar!
episodes.overview: In a very challenging cook, the contestants must make a sweet dish without using refined sugar.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test - Best Selling And Australia's Most Popular Ingredients
episodes.overview: This episode's mystery box holds some of the best-selling ingredients from Coles and along with these, contestants must cook with some of Australia's favourite ingredients: Vegemite, tomato sauce or Milo.

episodes.name: Pressure Test – Jock Zonfrillo
episodes.overview: This episode's challenge has been set by special guest Jock Zonfrillo from Restaurant Orana. Contestants must create dishes that showcase one of his favourite native ingredients.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge – Beluga Caviar & Phil Wood
episodes.overview: The three winners of the challenges must create a dish featuring Beluga caviar. The best dish will see its maker compete for an immunity pin against Pt Leo Estate chef Phil Wood.

episodes.name: Team Challenge – Best Diners & Best Ingredients
episodes.overview: The contestants must cook a four-course meal for the Best Diners In The World while showcasing the Best Ingredients In The Country. Little do they know, the diners are their loved ones.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Massimo Bottura
episodes.overview: The top 10 are joined by the world’s top chef Massimo Bottura and asked to cook with ingredients that are very close to Massimo’s heart: ones that are frequently disposed of.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test: Deja Vu
episodes.overview: This episode’s mystery box involves some deja vu and later, in the invention test, contestants have 60 minutes to create a dish that takes the judges to a moment in time that evokes a particular memory.

episodes.name: Pressure Test – Kirsten Tibballs
episodes.overview: Champion chocolatier Kirsten Tibballs is in the MasterChef kitchen for this episode's pressure test. Three contestants from the previous invention test must recreate Kirsten's apple pie. Who will be going home?

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge – Same Ingredients/Different Styles & Adam D’Sylva
episodes.overview: All contestants will cook with the same ingredient but in a different style. The winner of round one will be cooking against renowned chef Adam D'Sylva for the illustrious immunity pin.

episodes.name: Team Challenge – Q Train Vegetarian Course
episodes.overview: Aboard the Q Train travelling restaurant our contestants, in teams, must prepare a vegetarian course using oyster mushrooms, baby zucchini, eggplant or figs. The bottom two teams face elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge – Time Auction
episodes.overview: This episode is the return of the time auction where contestants bid for ingredients with time rather than money. The more time they spend buying ingredients, the less time they have to cook.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test - WA
episodes.overview: The remaining contestants fly to Western Australia for a mystery box challenge and later an invention test, using all the great produce WA has to offer.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Wildflower 5 Course Degustation
episodes.overview: At Wildflower Restaurant in Perth, contestants will cook a five-course degustation featuring an ingredient that chef Matt Sartori has selected.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge - Fast Track to Finals Week
episodes.overview: The winners from the previous two days now cook for an opportunity to fast-track themselves into Finals Week. Round two comes down to the wire as contestants are hungry for the win.

episodes.name: Team Challenge - Leeuwin Estate Safari Club
episodes.overview: This episode's setting is the beautiful Leeuwin Estate Safari Club in Margaret River. Guided by head chef Dan Gedge, our contestants will battle it out in a team challenge.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Santiago Fernandez & Masterclass
episodes.overview: This pressure test is set by Santiago Fernandez and it's a doozy. The stakes are high and the least impressive cook will be sent home. Plus, catch a masterclass showing off delicious recipes.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge & Invention Test – The Loved One’s Selection
episodes.overview: Each contestant has an ingredient chosen for them by a loved one, with the note explaining their choice. Later, the judges select an ingredient for each contestant to cook with in the invention test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test - The Lamington
episodes.overview: The chef director behind Dinner by Heston in Melbourne and London, Ashley Palmer-Watts, sets a lamington-themed pressure test. One contestant will be sent home with only days remaining in the competition.

episodes.name: Advantage Challenge - Top 5
episodes.overview: Our top five are battling to win an advantage for the next challenge, which could secure them a spot in the semifinal. Contestants can cook whatever they want and decide how much time is on the clock.

episodes.name: Top 5 Challenge - The Press Club
episodes.overview: Contestants are cooking at Press Club, the brainchild of judge George Calombaris. With the Press Club announcing it will soon close, the top five take to the kitchen to prepare one of the final meals.

episodes.name: Grand Final Week - Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: By the end of the episode, five will become four as the trophy beckons. In a special MasterClass, contestants set their very own mystery box challenge for the judges and Curtis Stone.

episodes.name: Semi Final with Peter Gilmore
episodes.overview: This semifinal is a pressure test set by acclaimed Quay executive chef Peter Gilmore. The three contestants who do the most impressive job recreating the dish will earn their spot in the grand finale.

episodes.name: Grand Final
episodes.overview: It's been months of nail-biting challenges, but there can only be one winner to walk away with the life-changing title of Australia's MasterChef 2019

episodes.name: Premiere: Immunity Challenge: Finale-Worthy Dish
episodes.overview: The highly anticipated cooking show is back for an incredible 12th season, with a tasty new recipe - and cooking legend Gordon Ramsay will be in the kitchen the ENTIRE first week!Returning to the MasterChef kitchen are 24 much-loved and respected former contestants, Although these familiar faces from the past 11 seasons have forged incredible careers in the food industry, they all have some unfinished business - they are back to win.

episodes.name: Team Challenge
episodes.overview: Each team must cook a three-course meal for 120 guests. The judges reveal three ingredients: black garlic, ginger and potatoes. Each team must feature one of the ingredients in each course.

episodes.name: Relay Style Team Challenge
episodes.overview: Teams must cook a three-course meal in a relay style cook. Each team member starts a course and after 20 minutes must swap to the next course. The most cohesive menu with the best dishes wins.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Keeping Up with Gordon
episodes.overview: After impressing the judges in the round robin relay challenge, the winning team are back in the kitchen cooking for immunity and a chance to be safe from the next elimination.

episodes.name: Gordon Ramsay's 90-Minute Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Every contestant is up for elimination, except the winner of the immunity challenge. The pressure mounts for all contestants to deliver delicious dishes and keep their place in the competition.

episodes.name: Ultimate BBQ Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants compete in the ultimate barbecue challenge, cooking for a staggering 1200 people. The team who least impresses will find themselves cooking in the pressure test.

episodes.name: Two-Round Pressure Test: Orana
episodes.overview: In the first pressure test of the season, contestants must cook three dishes from judge Jock Zonfrillo's three-hatted, award-winning restaurant, Orana. The least impressive dish will send someone home.

episodes.name: Melissa Leong's Mystery Box
episodes.overview: In the first mystery box challenge of the season, the 22 remaining contestants discover the ingredients have been chosen from all corners of the globe, by judge Melissa Leong.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Judges' Taste Test / MasterClass
episodes.overview: The five contestants with the most impressive dishes from yesterday's challenge find themselves back in the kitchen ready to cook off in an immunity challenge. Plus, MasterClass with Andy and Jock.

episodes.name: Judges' Ingredients Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: In this episode's elimination challenge, every contestant bar one, the winner of the immunity challenge, is up for elimination. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be going home.

episodes.name: 3-Round Team Showdown
episodes.overview: The contestants are split into three teams of seven and compete in a three-round cook-off. After the third round, the bottom six contestants are revealed and will cook off in the next episode's pressure test.

episodes.name: Self Pressure Test
episodes.overview: It's a pressure test with a difference. Each contestant has written their own pressure test recipe and has to create a dish to wow the judges. The least impressive dish will send its maker home.

episodes.name: Barter Mystery Box
episodes.overview: The judges reveal that each contestant's mystery box contains four ingredients which they can barter with one another for. The top four dishes will see their makers cook for immunity in the next episode.

episodes.name: Curtis Stone's Time Auction Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Today's immunity challenge with Curtis Stone sees four contestants compete in a MasterChef time auction. The more time they spend on buying ingredients, the less time they have to cook.

episodes.name: Textures Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: This challenge is all about texture. In round one, contestants must cook a dish with the best crunch. Round two is all about a gooey texture. The least impressive gooey dish will send its chef home.

episodes.name: Thai Team Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants leave the kitchen for a week of off-site challenges. Teams must make two entrees and three mains for 50 diners. The least impressive team faces a pressure test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Guess The Ingredients & Replicate The Dish
episodes.overview: Helly Raichura, of Enter Via Laundry, bases this taste test on her popular dish, 'pasta not pasta'. Contestants who guess the least ingredients correctly must replicate the dish in a challenge.

episodes.name: Locally Sourced Mystery Box
episodes.overview: This episode's ingredients are sourced by locals who grow fruit and vegetables in their backyards. The three most impressive dishes from the mystery box challenge will cook in an immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Sushi Train 100 Plate Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Three contestants are told they must prepare 100 small plates each, consisting of five different dishes. All dishes will be served on the sushi train and will be colour-coded in this blind tasting.

episodes.name: Take-Away Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: In today's take-away elimination challenge contestants must make a dish that will stand the home delivery test. Contestants have 90 minutes from the start of the cook to completed delivery.

episodes.name: Double Twist Team Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants learn that there will be a twist with every challenge this week, so they must think on their feet to survive another week in the MasterChef kitchen. Tonight two twists really stir the pot.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Darren Purchese's Passionfruit Pavlova
episodes.overview: Contestants have three hours to complete a simply stunning Darren Purchese dish, but in the final hour of the cook, a twist that no one could anticipate is thrown at the contestants.

episodes.name: Mystery Box - with a twist!
episodes.overview: Contestants have 75 minutes to cook a dish using one or more of the eight ingredients in the mystery box. The contestants are pushed to the limit when a twist is delivered to their benches.

episodes.name: Katy Perry Immunity Challenge & Masterclass
episodes.overview: Katy Perry guest judges a very special Hot 'N' Cold challenge to honour the iconic MasterChef theme song. The contestant with the best dish will find themselves safe from the elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination Cook-Off Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants are cooking off against the other contestant on their bench. The best dish from each bench will be safe, while the remaining contestants must cook in the elimination round.

episodes.name: Sweet or Savoury Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Jo Barrett and Matt Stone from Oakridge Wines mentor this service challenge, with each team cooking a sweet or savoury menu. The team with the least impressive menu faces the pressure test.

episodes.name: Peter Gunn's Black Box Elimination
episodes.overview: Contestants must replicate chef Peter Gunn's 'Black Box' from his restaurant Ides. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be going home.

episodes.name: Vegan Mystery Box
episodes.overview: Contestants must create a vegan dish using at least one ingredient from the mystery box set by vegan chef Shannon Martinez. The top four dishes will cook off in the next immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Instant Noodle Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: This episode's immunity challenge is fought in two rounds. In one round, contestants must create a delicious dish using instant noodles. The top two from round one must make a nostalgic and comforting dish.

episodes.name: Kingfish Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Josh Niland of The Fish Butchery breaks down a kingfish for each of the contestants to choose a cut to cook with. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be going home.

episodes.name: Two Dish Relay Challenge
episodes.overview: Each team must cook two dishes: one main and one dessert. Each contestant has 20 minutes to cook and they have just 45 seconds to hand over the dish to the next contestant in the relay.

episodes.name: Kirsten Tibballs' Meljito Dessert Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Queen of chocolate and guest chef Kirsten Tibballs reveals that, for the pressure test, the contestants must create her wow-factor dessert the meljito.

episodes.name: Family Photo Mystery Box
episodes.overview: The contestants lift the lids of their mystery box to find a photo sent by their loved ones. The contestants have 60 minutes to create a dish inspired by the memory in their family photo.

episodes.name: Fairytale Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants must create a dish inspired by one of seven classic fairytales. With an open pantry and garden, the contestant with the best dish and the strongest concept will win immunity.

episodes.name: Ice cream Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants must make a dish that has two different flavoured ice-creams that only work when they are eaten together. In round two, they must make a dish using one of five unusual flavour pairings.

episodes.name: Citrus Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants cook a sweet or savoury style dish championing a citrus fruit of their choice. In round two, they use the same fruit, but their dish must be in the opposite style.

episodes.name: Coskun Uysal's Meat/Protein Dessert Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Contestants discover they must create a dish inspired by chef Coskun Uysal's chicken rice pudding dessert. With this in mind, they must create their own dessert featuring a meat or protein.

episodes.name: Luck Of The Draw Mystery Box
episodes.overview: This episode's mystery box ingredients are decided entirely by the luck of the draw, with numbered lottery balls corresponding to 25 ingredients on display.

episodes.name: Highest Score Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Each round in this immunity challenge is worth 10 points and the contestant with the highest score at the end of round three will win immunity and be free from the upcoming elimination.

episodes.name: The Aussie Pressure Test
episodes.overview: It's an Australia-themed pressure test. First up contestants must cook a delicious savoury pie and sauce. The bottom four must then create a dish celebrating what Australia means to them.

episodes.name: Teams Of Two Communication Challenge
episodes.overview: Teams of two must create two dishes using a chosen ingredient. Dishes must be identical in taste and appearance, but they will not be able to see each other while they cook, so communication is key.

episodes.name: Benjamin Cooper Jungle CurryPressure Test
episodes.overview: Benjamin Cooper, Executive Chef of Chin Chin Melbourne, sets tonight's pressure test where contestants must recreate his jungle curry with rice and roti without a recipe.

episodes.name: Smokin' Mystery Box
episodes.overview: Today's mystery box is all about smoke. Contestants can use any method of smoking as long as one element has been smoked with a smoking gun. The top four will cook in tomorrow's immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Pumpkin Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Today's immunity challenge is all about resourcefulness. The contestants are each presented with a pumpkin and have 90 minutes to cook three dishes that feature the pumpkin in some way.

episodes.name: Atlas Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Charlie Carrington of Melbourne restaurant Atlas sets this elimination challenge, focusing on food from different countries. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be sent home.

episodes.name: The Golden Mystery Box
episodes.overview: With new rules this week, a contestant will be going home every three days! Today, the chefs use the contents of a very shiny Mystery Box to create a dish that makes them stand out.

episodes.name: 5 Minute Ingredient Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Every five minutes an ingredient that can be used in their cook is revealed to our contestants. They can start cooking at any time but only have access to the ingredients revealed up to that point.

episodes.name: Blind Taste Test Elimination
episodes.overview: This elimination will take place over two rounds, the first of which is the classic blind taste test. The first four contestants who guess incorrectly will go into round two.

episodes.name: Use Everything Mystery Box!
episodes.overview: The judges reveal that the contestants need to use all the ingredients in their mystery box to create two dishes - a sweet and savoury dish - in 75 minutes.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Three heavy hitters of the competition go head-to-head. Who will make top six?

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge - Top 6
episodes.overview: In today's elimination contestants are challenged to cook a classic dish. Could this be Reynold's final cook in the MasterChef kitchen?

episodes.name: Colour Inspired Mystery Box
episodes.overview: Today's mystery box is inspired by colour. The dish can be sweet or savoury and contestants can access the pantry with the garden also in play. So why is Melissa so emotional?

episodes.name: Cloche Choice Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: In the battle for top five, contestants must choose two cloches and cook with the ingredients underneath. They can give up one cloche and select a third, however they must cook with the third ingredient.

episodes.name: Phil Wood Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Phil Wood, from two of Victoria's finest restaurants, reveals that round one is a pressure test. Contestants have 75 minutes to replicate his dish: potatoes duchess with shiitake mushrooms and cauliflower.

episodes.name: Last Chance For Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The race to finals week is on! The makers of the top three dishes from the mystery box challenge will battle it out for one last chance at winning immunity this season.

episodes.name: No Rules Challenge
episodes.overview: Who will make the finals? With no set rules in place, the contestants must mutually decide the cook time to create a dish, sweet or savoury, that best proves to the judges they have come back to win.

episodes.name: Mammoth Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: In this mammoth elimination challenge, the contestants discover not only will they be cooking a four-course meal for the MasterChef judges, but for six of the hottest chefs in the country.

episodes.name: The Union Jack Mystery Box
episodes.overview: The contestants discover the mystery box, covered in a Union Jack flag, has been set by guest chef Gordon Ramsay.

episodes.name: Ordinary or Extraordinary Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: In this elimination challenge, contestants must choose to use either ingredients from an ordinary pantry or an extraordinary pantry.

episodes.name: SemiFinal - Three Becomes Two
episodes.overview: In the semifinal challenge, our top three contestants compete for a place in the Grand Final. At the end of this challenge, three become two.

episodes.name: Grand Final
episodes.overview: After a long culinary journey the two finalists are competing for a $250,000 cash prize and the title of MasterChef Australia 2020.

12.name: Season 12
12.overview:
Jock Zonfrillo, Melissa Leong and Andy Allen take the helm of the show that celebrates food and the love of food.

Jock, Melissa and Andy will be joined in the MasterChef Australia kitchen by a delicious assortment of the world’s best chefs, including Gordon Ramsay, Heston Blumenthal and Curtis Stone, to serve up the 12th helping of MasterChef Australia. The traditional MasterChef Australia recipe also boasts some new ingredients when the best of the best from the past 11 seasons return to the kitchen in MasterChef Australia – Back To Win.

episodes.name: Auditions, Day 1
episodes.overview: The best home cooks from around the country will face challenge after challenge to see who will rise to the top and take home the coveted title of Australia's next MasterChef.

episodes.name: Auditions, Day 2
episodes.overview: The judges are looking for just five more cooks to round out the top 24. The home cooks who are given a second chance will battle it out for the remaining aprons.

episodes.name: Emelia Jackson Mystery Box
episodes.overview: This mystery box is selected by MasterChef Australia champion Emelia Jackson. The three best dishes will be awarded an immunity pin that can be played at any time during an elimination cook.

episodes.name: Chicken Or The Egg?
episodes.overview: In this two round challenge, contestants must create dishes that feature a chicken or an egg. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be the first sent home.

episodes.name: Superstars Week - Nigella Lawason
episodes.overview: Superstars Week kicks off with Nigella Lawson. Contestants must recreate Nigella's favourite dish based on her detailed description, with no ingredient list, recipe or visual reference to work from.

episodes.name: Superstars Week - Yotam Ottolenghi
episodes.overview: Yotam Ottolenghi presents his favourite flavour bombs: numbing oil, fenugreek marinade and chipotle peanuts. Each team must create a meal that features one of Yotam's flavour bombs.

episodes.name: Superstars Week - Massimo Bottura (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: The judges reveal this elimination challenge is over two rounds and is set by cooking legend Massimo Bottura. Massimo presents his take on the classic dish: mac and cheese.

episodes.name: Superstars Week - Clare Smyth (Mystery Box)
episodes.overview: Clare Smyth reveals the dish that has inspired her choice of mystery box ingredients. Contestants must create a sweet or savoury dish using the ingredients that Clare has chosen for the mystery box.

episodes.name: Superstars Week - Heston Blumenthal (Immunity Challenge)
episodes.overview: Heston Blumenthal sets an immunity challenge in which contestants must use a popular breakfast ingredient to create a delicious dessert.

episodes.name: Poh, Callum & Reynold (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: MasterChef alumni Poh, Callum and Reynold present the contestants with three dishes from their venues. Contestants must create a dish worthy of a place on the menu at any of these establishments.

episodes.name: Least & Most Comfortable (Team Challenge)
episodes.overview: Each team must cook the same six dishes within the time allocated. Each contestant on the team will cook one of the dishes and will be judged against the same dish made by the other two teams.

episodes.name: Sweet & Savoury Tart (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: Each contestant must choose the dish they feel most comfortable making: a savoury tart or sweet tart. Jock then switches the dishes and contestants must cook the dish they're least comfortable with.

episodes.name: Staples (Immunity Challenge)
episodes.overview: Contestants must create a dish using the staple ingredients under their benches as well as two ingredients from the garden for flavour. Contestants with the top five dishes will compete for immunity.

episodes.name: Choose Your Ingredient & Masterclass
episodes.overview: Contestants must choose an ingredient they would like to feature in a dish, but they won't know the ingredient they must pair it with until they have locked in their choice. A Masterclass follows.

episodes.name: That's The Way The Cookie Crumbles (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: Keen as mustard, the contestants have to cook a dish that interprets one of the classic food sayings on display. The contestant who fails will be going home. That's the way the cookie crumbles.

episodes.name: Meet The Masters
episodes.overview: It's Meet the Masters Week. This opportunity gives the contestants up-close insights into the skills of the best culinary masters in Australia.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: The least impressive team from the master team challenge must cook off in this pressure test.

episodes.name: Mystery Box
episodes.overview: The contestants enter the kitchen ready to take on the mystery box challenge set by a Michelin-starred chef.

episodes.name: Cooking With Fire (Immunity Challenge)
episodes.overview: In a very special challenge, the top four contestants from the previous challenge meet in the kitchen to be taught a lesson in cooking with fire. The most impressive cook wins immunity.

episodes.name: Meet The Masters (Elimination)
episodes.overview: For the final cook of Meet the Masters Week, the bottom four contestants must make a dish that demonstrates how they have mastered a skill, flavour or technique they have learnt across the week.

episodes.name: Service Brigade - Tonka (Immunity Challenge)
episodes.overview: Andy reveals that every challenge this week will be a service challenge and all 16 contestants are in with a chance at winning immunity from Sunday's elimination.

episodes.name: Service Challenge - Movida (Immunity Challenge)
episodes.overview: This challenge is all about the ingredients. Each team must feature the same ingredient in each course

episodes.name: Service Challenge - (Immunity Challenge)
episodes.overview: For this challenge, two pantries are on offer: a European pantry and an Eastern pantry. By the toss of a coin, the team that win the toss get to choose their desired pantry.

episodes.name: Service Challenge - (Immunity Challenge)
episodes.overview: Each team has two-and-a-half hours to cook a three-course meal and each course must champion a colour chosen by the toss of a coin.

episodes.name: Team Challenge
episodes.overview: Each team must create a dish that features the ingredient hidden underneath the tablecloth and must also use an allocated electrical appliance at some stage during the cook.

episodes.name: Vegetable Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants must choose from either a potato, broccoli, carrot, brown onion or zucchini, to make a delicious dish featuring the vegetable of choice, but not necessarily a vegetarian dish.

episodes.name: Pressure Test
episodes.overview: In this pressure test, it's a fight to stay in the competition and four contestants must re-create a dish without ever seeing it.

episodes.name: 11 Utensils
episodes.overview: The contestants must create a dish using only the 11 utensils in the mystery box. The dish can be sweet or savoury, with an open pantry and access to the garden.

episodes.name: Hot Chillies! (Immunity Challenge)
episodes.overview: The contestants must cook a dish using some of the hottest chillies in the world. The dish that best highlights the heat and flavour of their chilli will win immunity.

episodes.name: Game ID (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: This elimination is played over two rounds. In the first round, contestants must identify the 14 game meats on display. The six contestants with the lowest scores will cook off in round two.

episodes.name: Second Chance Week
episodes.overview: It's Second Chance Week in the MasterChef kitchen. Across the week, 11 previously eliminated contestants are back with not one, but two chances to get back in the competition.

episodes.name: Second Chance Week (Pressure Test)
episodes.overview: Renowned pastry chef Anthony Hart reveals his pressure test dish: chocolate oasis. The contestants have 2 hours and 15 minutes, plus a further eight minutes to plate up Anthony's creation.

episodes.name: Clear Or Hidden (Mystery Box Challenge)
episodes.overview: This episode, the 10 returning contestants can choose between a clear mystery box where the ingredients are visible or a regular mystery box where the ingredients are hidden.

episodes.name: It's A Knockout
episodes.overview: Four contestants are told they will have two-and-a-half hours to prepare a three-course menu. But the catch is that after each course is tasted, one contestant will be knocked out of the competition.

episodes.name: Murray Cod (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: Josh Niland demonstrates how to make the most of a Murray cod utilising the entire fish. For this challenge, contestants are given one Murray cod and must use the same fish for up to three rounds.

episodes.name: Pair Up With Crayfish
episodes.overview: Contestants must pair up with another contestant to form seven teams. Each team must create crayfish two ways, one familiar dish and one inventive dish, utilising the freshly caught crayfish.

episodes.name: Vego (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: The four contestants cooking in this elimination challenge discover they will be cooking a vegetarian dish, with all ingredients harvested fresh from Dairy Flat Farm in Daylesford.

episodes.name: Melbourne Inspiration (Mystery Box)
episodes.overview: The mystery box reveals a map of Melbourne and a camera phone to take pictures. The contestants must explore the city streets and laneways to take a picture that will inspire their dish.

episodes.name: Kate Reid Pastry
episodes.overview: Jock introduces Kate Reid, the mastermind behind Lune Croissanterie. Contestants must use Kate's world-class pastry and turn it into a dish that is not a croissant.

episodes.name: 90 Minute Cook Time (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: The contestants must decide how much of their 90-minute cook time they use in round one, because they will only have the remainder of that time to cook in round two.

episodes.name: Home Delivery (Team Challenge)
episodes.overview: Teams must create a three-course home delivery menu and can choose any theme or cuisine for their menu. Each team has three hours to produce 60 serves.

episodes.name: Khanh Nguyen's Pork Wellington
episodes.overview: Guest chef Khanh Nguyen from Sunda has taken South-East Asian food to the next level. The contestants must create Khanh's dish: pork wellington with lattice crackling and flavours of banh mi.

episodes.name: 4 Ingredient Barter (Mystery Box)
episodes.overview: Jock reveals this mystery box is different. Contestants need to use four ingredients in their final dish, but before the cook starts, they can barter for the ingredients from each other.

episodes.name: The Top Four (Immunity Challenge)
episodes.overview: The top four cooks from the latest mystery box challenge battle it out for immunity and a guaranteed spot in the top 10.

episodes.name: Nu Nu Ingredient ID (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: Contestants must correctly identify ingredients in three dishes from Nick Holloway's Nu Nu menu. The five contestants who name the least amount of ingredients correctly will cook off in round two.

episodes.name: Three Blue Ducks (Service Challenge)
episodes.overview: The top 10 contestants arrive at URBNSURF, the home to Australia's first ever surf park in Melbourne's west to discover they will be running Andy Allen's restaurant, Three Blue Ducks.

episodes.name: Darren Purchese (Pressure Test)
episodes.overview: Contestants must cook a sweet pressure test recipe of their own design. Darren Purchese will be running the floor and mentoring the contestants and the judges will do a blind tasting of each dish.

episodes.name: Family Messages
episodes.overview: After watching emotional messages from their family members, Melissa explains that contestants must make a dish inspired by their family. The top two dishes will cook in tomorrow's immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Keep Up With Curtis & Masterclass
episodes.overview: In today's challenge, the contestants must keep up with Curtis Stone as he cooks his ultimate roast chicken dish. Andy, Jock and chef Nornie Bero show off their skills in a delicious Masterclass.

episodes.name: Black Mystery Box or Black Gloche? (Double Elimination)
episodes.overview: Today there is a massive double elimination. Contestants must choose between cooking with the black mystery box or the black cloche, with the ingredients only revealed when they make their choice.

episodes.name: Uluru
episodes.overview: Today we are in the spiritual heart of Australia, Uluru. Contestants must create a fine dining three-course meal under the stars at the stunning Field of Light installation for 25 diners plus judges.

episodes.name: Simpson's Gap (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: The team arrive at Simpson's Gap and judges reveal the contestants must create a dish using a variety of foraged bush foods. The contestant with the least impressive dish will be sent home.

episodes.name: All 7 Ingredients! (Mystery Box Challenge)
episodes.overview: In the toughest mystery box challenge of the season, the contestants discover they must create a dish using all seven ingredients under the mystery box.

episodes.name: The Cloche Challenge
episodes.overview: Each cloche represents an ingredient, a cuisine, food related word, or kitchen equipment. The contestants must choose any two cloches and feature whatever is under the cloche in their dish.

episodes.name: Fast Food & Fancy Food (Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: Contestants must choose an ingredient and cook it two ways, in a fast-food and in a fancy food application. The contestants with the three least impressive fast-food dishes will cook in round two.

episodes.name: Society (Service & Elimination Challenge)
episodes.overview: The judges welcome the contestants to Martin Benn's opulent new Melbourne restaurant, Society. The pressure is on as they discover today's service challenge is also an elimination.

episodes.name: Vue Du Monde - Bottlebrush (Pressure Test)
episodes.overview: Contestants face a pressure test like no other. Chef Hugh Allen from restaurant Vue Du Monde, challenges contestants to recreate his dish, bottlebrush, mum's gum nuts and billy buttons.

episodes.name: Finalists (Advantage Challenge)
episodes.overview: The finalists enter the MasterChef kitchen to discover the day's advantage challenge, which will see the winner cooking in the Finale.

episodes.name: Semi-Final
episodes.overview: Contestants compete in a semifinal service challenge. The contestant with the least impressive menu will leave the competition. Finalists are joined by returning contestants for the final MasterClass.

episodes.name: Grand Finale (Part 1)
episodes.overview: It’s here, the MasterChef Australia Grand Finale for 2021. Our three finalists face an incredible three round challenge over two days with a total of 140 points up for grabs.

episodes.name: Grand Finale (Part 2)
episodes.overview: It’s day two of the epic MasterChef Australia Grand Finale for 2021 and the contestant who scores the most points overall will win the title of MasterChef 2021 and walk away with $250,000.

13.name: Season 13
13.overview:
Judges Jock Zonfrillo, Melissa Leong and Andy Allen are back in the MasterChef Australia kitchen, ready to introduce the next generation of exceptional home cooks. 2021 will be seasoned to perfection with some of the world’s most recognisable and beloved chefs including Nigella Lawson, Yotam Ottolenghi, Heston Blumenthal, Massimo Bottura and Clare Smyth - plus homegrown sensations including Curtis Stone, Kirsten Tibballs, Darren Purchese, Alla Wolf-Tasker, Scott Pickett, Poh Ling Yeow, Callum Hann and Reynold Poernomo, all set to challenge the top 24 contestants.

Sacrificing everything to follow their food dreams, this season’s passionate contestants have put their lives on hold to be part of this life-changing experience. With heart, soul and drive, this season’s exceptional contestants will follow their food dreams and make magic happen.

episodes.name: Meet the Fans & Favourites
episodes.overview: 12 emerging home cooks will experience the magic of the MasterChef kitchen for the very first time, while 12 of MasterChef Australia’s most loved contestants will feel a sense of nostalgia as they walk through the hallowed doors for a second time. Whether their passion stems from feeding their family, creating culinary masterpieces on TikTok or a desire to test their skills against some of the best cooks MasterChef Australia has ever produced, these 24 contestants from all over Australia share one common love – food.

episodes.name: 1st Service Challenge
episodes.overview: In a massive service challenge, it's Fans versus Favourites, course versus course in the ultimate three-course battle, with the winning teams heading to the immunity decider challenge.

episodes.name: 1st Team Challenge
episodes.overview: Split into four teams across four benches, 12 contestants discover they have 75 minutes on the clock to create a dish using the ingredients from a particular layer of the balanced diet food pyramid.

episodes.name: 1st Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: It's this season's first immunity challenge. Choosing ingredients from mystery cloches, the contestant with the best dish wins immunity and will sit out the elimination challenge.

episodes.name: The Jaffle Elimination - 1st Elimination
episodes.overview: It's the first elimination of the year. The makers of the best jaffle in round one will be safe, but the chef with the least-satisfying dish that changed their life in round two will go home.

episodes.name: The Very First Mystery Box
episodes.overview: Contestants must create a dish using the same ingredients that were in the very first mystery box in MasterChef season one, The least impressive fare will send their chefs to a pressure test cook-off.

episodes.name: Adriano Zumbo Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Dessert king Adriano Zumbo returns to the kitchen for a pressure test like no other. The contestant with the least impressive take on Zumbo's Polly Want A Waffle will be sent home.

episodes.name: Team Relay Challenge + 1st Masterclass
episodes.overview: Four teams vie for a shot at immunity in the infamous team relay challenge. This time, teams won't even know the mystery ingredient until the clock starts ticking! Plus, the first Masterclass of 2022.

episodes.name: Beat The Chef Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The winning team in the previous relay challenge join the top-two mystery box winners for a chance at immunity as they try to Beat The Chef, who just happens to be MasterChef favourite Matt Stone.

episodes.name: Bonjour - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Bonjour. Get ready for this episode's classic service challenge with guest chef Shannon Bennett. Each team must cook a French-inspired entree, main and dessert for 20 diners plus the judges.

episodes.name: Fridge & Pantry - Mystery Box
episodes.overview: Guest chef Shannon Bennett returns with 10 of his favourite fridge and pantry items to create this mystery box. The two least impressive cooks will face off in the next episode's pressure test.

episodes.name: Noi - Pressure Test
episodes.overview: MasterChef alumni and dessert king Reynold Poernomo returns to set this pressure test dish: his new intricate signature dessert, noi. The chef who fails to cope with the dish will be sent home.

episodes.name: Fast vs Fancy - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Guest chef Curtis Stone leads teams out to the garden for a fast food versus fancy food service. With 80 ravenous diners waiting, the winners will head to the next immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Ingredients vs Time - Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Guest chef Curtis Stone returns as contestants cook a tasty dish worthy of immunity. But in this classic challenge, as their pantry of ingredients increases, their cooking time decreases.

episodes.name: Eggscellant Elimination
episodes.overview: Who will crack in an 'eggscellent' elimination challenge that sees contestants given just one egg to create the tastiest dish? Fail, and they must scramble to cook for their lives in round 2.

episodes.name: The Alphabet Of Mystery Boxes
episodes.overview: Twenty-six alphabetical mystery boxes contain single ingredients that correspond with the letter on the box. Chefs must cook using their designated ingredient, with the bottom four headed for a pressure test.

episodes.name: Fat Duck Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Fat Duck pastry chef Gareth Whitton sets this pressure test with his smoked pecan and butterscotch tart. The dish that least resembles Gareth's creation will send its maker home.

episodes.name: Clare Smyth Service Challenge
episodes.overview: London's celebrated chef Clare Smyth has selected cherries and honey as two core ingredients that teams will need to cook with in this service challenge, as they duke it out for a shot at immunity.

episodes.name: Summer Cucumbers
episodes.overview: The winners from yesterday's service challenge compete in a two-round immunity challenge. The contestant who creates the two most impressive dishes will dodge Sunday's elimination bullet.

episodes.name: The Overnight Dish Elimination
episodes.overview: It's elimination day and the creator of the best Round 1 fare will keep their team safe. Those fighting to avoid the drop must then prepare a tasty dish to be left overnight and cooked the next day.

episodes.name: The Coffee Mystery Box
episodes.overview: In a grungy Fitzroy warehouse, contestants lift the lids on their mystery boxes, leading to coffee beans spilling out across their bench as judges reveal they must create a dish that features coffee.

episodes.name: Alla Wolf-Tasker's Re-creation Elimination
episodes.overview: Arriving at Alla Wolf-Tasker's Lake House restaurant, contestants must re-create his summer cucumbers with Murray cod dish. The contestant whose dish least resembles Alla's will be going home.

episodes.name: Date Night Team Challenge
episodes.overview: Teams need to create the prefect date night meal including an entree, main and dessert for 25 couples plus the judges. The two teams with the least impressive menu will head to a shock elimination.

episodes.name: Elimination & MasterClass
episodes.overview: The bottom two teams from the previous challenge face elimination and must split their 90-minute cooking time over two rounds, with the creator of the least impressive second round dish going home.

episodes.name: Two Cuisines Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: It's time to switch things up, and everyone is now cooking for themselves to stay in the competition. The maker of the best dish will win a cash prize of $10,000 and a game-changing immunity pin.

episodes.name: Not-So-Humble Invention Test
episodes.overview: The mystery box has been set by the queen of the kitchen, the legendary Maggie Beer. The four least impressive dishes created from the mystery box will send their makers into a pressure test.

episodes.name: Tuna Wellington Pressure test
episodes.overview: Fish butcher extraordinaire Josh Niland reveals his first pressure test dish: tuna wellington with mashed potato and tuna gravy. Whoever cooks the dish that is least like Josh's will be sent home

episodes.name: Werribee Mansion Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Teams face a service challenge for 60 hungry diners at the stately Werribee Mansion. To win a shot at immunity, contestants must turn humble ingredients into a fine dining entree and posh main course

episodes.name: Air Fryer immunity/Elimination
episodes.overview: Contestants vie for immunity from elimination over a two-round fry-up, and must create the best dishes using an everyday air fryer before cooking a sweet or savoury dish using a deep fryer.

episodes.name: Celebrate Greens Elimination
episodes.overview: Competitors must identify a selection of leafy greens and herbs. The first six contestants to incorrectly name the produce must create their tastiest dish that celebrates greens to avoid elimination.

episodes.name: Rainy Day Mystery Box
episodes.overview: Andy opens the mystery box to reveal a mini storm cloud as lightning flashes around the kitchen. Contestants must create a dish for a rainy day, with a fast track to the immunity challenge at stake.

episodes.name: 'Honey' Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Gelato master Donny Toce presents his intricate dessert, Honey, comprising a honey tuille, gelato honeycomb, and blown sugar beehive for this Pressure Test, and failure will send someone home.

episodes.name: Creative Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants become artists for a creative service challenge, and the judges expect three-course masterpieces as they take inspiration from a virtual forest at digital art gallery The LUME.

episodes.name: Marco Pierre White Pressure Test & MasterClass
episodes.overview: An imposing figure appears in the kitchen: iconic chef Marco Pierre White. Contestants face a pressure test to win immunity by recreating his panache of sea scallops, calamari and ink sauce.

episodes.name: Marco Pierre White Elimination
episodes.overview: Contestants must create a dish using ingredients from culinary king Marco Pierre White's array of pantry items that he uses at home. The least impressive dish will ensure elimination for its maker.

episodes.name: Smoking Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants enter the kitchen for a smoking mystery box challenge. They must create a dish that incorporates a burnt element or has the flavour of fire, for a shot at a huge advantage.

episodes.name: Elimination Pressure Test
episodes.overview: It's an elimination pressure test with a difference. The contestants won't see or taste the dish, and they won't be given a recipe. All they have to go on is a review written by judge Melissa Leong.

episodes.name: Immunity 3 Course Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Vying for a shot at immunity, contestants are split into two teams for a service challenge. Each team must curate a three-course menu for either the Japanese or Italian restaurant they are cooking in.

episodes.name: Movie Food Immunity
episodes.overview: You have a ticket to the silver screen for a movie food immunity challenge. After a popcorn taste test, the remaining competitors must create a blockbuster flavour choc-top that will thrill filmgoers.

episodes.name: Rick Stein Elimination
episodes.overview: Someone will be eliminated and miss out on the top 10 as contestants attempt to create an entrancing dish that transports the judges and legendary guest chef Rick Stein to a special place.

episodes.name: Top Ten Week Mystery Box
episodes.overview: Top 10 Week kicks off with one tough mystery box: it's the everything box, and all ingredients inside must be used. Plus, anyone who cooks a top dish this week will be safe from elimination.

episodes.name: Own Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Contestants have been asked to write their own Pressure Test overnight. Now, they must handle their own pressure and exceed the high bar they have set for themselves and bring their best dish yet.

episodes.name: Classic Invention Test
episodes.overview: This challenge is the classic invention test. Our cooks must be inventive, creative and able to think outside the box as they reimagine a classic we all grew up with: the humble fruit salad.

episodes.name: Time Auction
episodes.overview: The cooks with the four top dishes this week have won immunity from Sunday's elimination. Now they battle it out to win the final immunity pin, but only if they can ace the infamous Time Auction!

episodes.name: 3 Round Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Six contestants are cooking to survive in a challenge played out over three rounds, where they can only pick one ingredient to use: pumpkin, chicken or fish. What would you cook to stay in the game?

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: In a Mystery Box challenge that focuses on detail, plating and using what's available from a choice of tiny ingredients, cooks must plate up a winning entree-sized dish to avoid a Pressure Test.

episodes.name: 99 Ingredient Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Chef Khanh Nguyen reveals his seafood plate for today's Pressure Test, and there are 99 ingredients, 143 steps and 13 pages in the recipe! The chef whose dish least resembles Khanh's will go home.

episodes.name: Cooking For Your Loved Ones
episodes.overview: In today's service challenge, contestants are cooking for their loved ones, and must serve an entree, main and dessert. The team with the best menu will win a shot at tomorrow's immunity challenge.

episodes.name: Tame The Prickly Ingredient
episodes.overview: This episode's challenge is to tame one of these very prickly ingredients: chestnuts, stinging nettle, prickly pear or sea urchin. The best dish will win its maker immunity from the week's elimination.

episodes.name: Hugh Allen Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Seven contestants cook to avoid elimination. Over two rounds, using ingredients selected by guest chef Hugh Allen, competitors must create dishes impressive enough to see them through to safety.

episodes.name: Rainbow Mystery Box
episodes.overview: Contestants cook from a rainbow mystery box including painted crayfish, scampi caviar, Fruit Loops, dragon fruit, coloured corn, mukhwas, flowering pineapple sage, rainbow chard, and dried turmeric.

episodes.name: Kirsten Tibballs' Pressure Test
episodes.overview: For this pressure test, Chocolate Queen Kirsten Tibballs presents her intricate cherry on top dessert. The dish that least replicates Kirsten's delicious dessert will send its maker home.

episodes.name: The TWO Challenge
episodes.overview: Split into teams of two, contestants select two ingredients from two pantries, but can't see what their teammate is choosing. Teams will cook a dish using their four ingredients for a shot at immunity.

episodes.name: Ingredient Purchase Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants purchase their ingredients, using time as their currency. The more ingredients they purchase, the less time on the clock. For an immunity taste, they have no time to waste.

episodes.name: Finals Week - Oyster Challenge
episodes.overview: Finals Week sees our six finalists travel to Oyster Bay in Tasmania, where they will face a two-round oyster challenge. They'll need to be super creative to avoid being shucked out of the competition.

episodes.name: Finals Week - Truffle Immunity
episodes.overview: As their Tassie tour rolls on, the final five visit Deloraine for a truffle hunt. They'll then use the black diamonds they dug out of the ground to cook the most delicious dish worthy of immunity.

episodes.name: Finals Week - Final 4 - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: With one contestant holding immunity, the remaining four face elimination as they visit Tasmania's Lawrenny Distillery, where they must choose a spirit to showcase in a four-course service challenge.

episodes.name: Back In The Kitchen Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Back in the MasterChef kitchen following their Tasmanian adventure, contestants learn that the winner of this two-round immunity challenge will be fast-tracked straight through to the semifinal.

episodes.name: Final MasterClass
episodes.overview: It's time for some fun in MasterClass. The tables are turned as Jock and Andy go head-to-head in a pub meal invention test, before engaging in a three-course menu battle against our four finalists.

episodes.name: Peter Gilmore Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Peter Gilmore has created some of the most famed and punishing pressure tests in the program's history. For a spot in the semifinals, contestants must simultaneously cook two of his most complex dishes.

episodes.name: 2022 Semi Final
episodes.overview: Shannon Bennett is back for the semifinal, running the pass and offering advice. Contestants must create a three-course menu worthy of a place in the Finale for 20 diners each plus the judges.

episodes.name: 2022 GRAND FINAL
episodes.overview: Welcome to the Grand Final! Our two gifted finalists enter the kitchen for the last time and they'll have to impress Heston Blumenthal and our judges to win the title of MasterChef 2022 and $250,000.

14.name: Fans & Favourites
14.overview:
Jock Zonfrillo, Andy Allen and Melissa Leong return to judge Season 14 of MasterChef Australia: Fans & Favourites.

Original champion Julie Goodwin leads the 12 returning cooks who compete alongside 12 newcomers (and no auditions). The MasterChef kitchen also once again plays host to chefs from Australia and overseas, including Adriano Zumbo, Shannon Bennet, Curtis Stone, Reynold Poernomo, Clare Smyth, Alla Wolf-Tasker, Josh Niland and Maggie Beer.

episodes.name: Secrets & Surprises with Jamie Oliver
episodes.overview: Expect the unexpected with a season of secrets and surprises. Judges Melissa Leong, Jock Zonfrillo and Andy Allen are joined by special guest Jamie Oliver.

episodes.name: 15 Minute Dish & Keeping Up With Jamie
episodes.overview:
Jamie Oliver is back for another day in the MasterChef Australia kitchen!

Contestants must bring their A-game if they want to secure one of two spots in the first Immunity challenge of the season.

episodes.name: Surprise Flavour Bomb
episodes.overview: There's a catch to the flavour bombs that Jamie Oliver has left behind for the contestants to cook with today - they will only be revealed 15 minutes into the cook and must be included in the dish.

episodes.name: Beat The Chef
episodes.overview: Contestants must raid Shannon Bennett's fridge to create the tastiest dish in 45 minutes. The winner will go head-to-head with Vue de monde's Hugh Allen in the hope of winning an elusive immunity pin.

episodes.name: Childhood Ingredients
episodes.overview: Contestants fight to stay alive in the first elimination challenge of the season. Cooking from favourite childhood memories, the least impressive dishes over two rounds will send its maker home.

episodes.name: Poh's Plus Mystery Box
episodes.overview:
This season's first Mystery Box sees fan favourite Poh Ling Yeow back in the MasterChef kitchen for one night only.

Contestants must create a winning dish with just under bench staples and little else.

episodes.name: If The Choux Fits
episodes.overview: Former MasterChef winner and dessert queen Emelia Jackson is here to share her secrets. Using Emelia's choux pastry recipe, contestants must create a superb sweet or savoury dish to avoid elimination.

episodes.name: Matt vs Sashi
episodes.overview: Get your orders ready, its time for the first Service Challenge of the season. Two teams, aided by mentors Matt Sinclair and Sashi Cheliah, must cook an entree and a main course dish for 30 diners.

episodes.name: Andy's Chook & Beat the Chef
episodes.overview: Winner winner chicken dinner! Contestants must turn Andy's spit roasted chooks into a banger dish, with the winner cooking off for an Immunity Pin against Three Blue Ducks chef, Darren Robertson.

episodes.name: Julie's Soup
episodes.overview: MasterChef royalty Julie Goodwin returns, and survival is on the menu. Those who pick a wrong ingredient in Julie's seafood stew must cook to avoid elimination using only the items in Julie's recipe.

episodes.name: Big Week - Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: Big Week lives up to its name as the contents of MasterChef's biggest ever Mystery Box are revealed. Contestants must think outside the box and big up the flavour to avoid tomorrow's Pressure Test.

episodes.name: Tokyo Lamington Tower - Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Pressure Test elimination looms as three contestants strive to replicate Eddie Stewart's Tokyo Lamington Tower, featuring Snickers, strawberry matcha, charcoal pumpkin and yuzu curd meringue flavours.

episodes.name: Grazeland - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: As thousands of hungry punters descend on Melbourne's hip Grazeland, it's surf and turf for the masses with two teams vying for a shot at Immunity in MasterChef's biggest ever service challenge!

episodes.name: Mystery Appliance - Immunity Pin Challenge
episodes.overview: With an Immunity Pin at stake, whoever creates the best dish with a mystery appliance in round one will earn first pick of flavour pairings and a 15 minute head start against guest chef Sergio Perera.

episodes.name: 2 Day Elimination - Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Slow and steady keeps their place! Facing elimination, contestants embark on a two-day challenge with 45 minutes to marinate, pickle, brine and more in an overnight cook to finish off the next day.

episodes.name: Breakfast Cereals - Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants try to bowl the judges over by elevating humble breakfast cereals into nostalgic classics. Who will cry over spilt milk with a Pressure Test awaiting the worst cereal offenders tomorrow?

episodes.name: Viennetta Ice Cream Cake - Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Guest chef Donato Toce reveals his superb Viennetta ice cream cake. Pressure Test contestants will need ice in their veins to replicate the nostalgic dessert or risk being frozen out of the kitchen.

episodes.name: Sweet....Or Sour? - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Two teams must wok hard to create a sumptuous banquet at a suburban Chinese Restaurant as they hope to takeaway a crack at Immunity. Will our judges deem their plates of fortune to be sweet ... or sour?

episodes.name: Gabriel Gate - Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Great frypans of fire! It's an Immunity Pin fracas as a field of faves fan the flames in a flipping flambe free-for-all. Who will face fab French foodie Gabriel Gate in a fierce fight to the finish?

episodes.name: Trip Down Memory Lane - Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Fancy a final trip down memory lane for a '70s-themed dinner party? A little fermented curd will do the trick! Then, time travel for the taste buds leads to a tearful farewell to one contestant.

episodes.name: Home Cooks vs Pro Cooks - Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: It's home cooks versus pro cooks in a culinary smackdown. The gloves are off as three contenders go toe-to-toe with Jacqui Challinor and her Nomad Restaurant warriors. Who will deliver the knockout blow?

episodes.name: Best Of The Best - Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Three more contestants battle the best of the best, dueling with Nick Holloway's Nu Nu crew in a mind-blowing three-course Pressure Test whipped up by Aru and Sunda Restaurant's gifted chef, Khahn Nguyen.

episodes.name: Louis Tikaram Blind Relay - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Louis Tikaram and his Stanley Restaurant team sprint to the kitchen for a blind relay against three MasterChef contestants. With no handovers and zero communication... who will be the runaway winners?

episodes.name: Shock Rock Around The Clock - Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Who can knock Jock's socks off in a shock rock around the clock? Three cooks face the chopping block against Serai's flock. Time is docked for the best stock. Tick tock, tick tock, don't get crocked!

episodes.name: Rick Stein - Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Our home cooks are wading into treacherous waters as global seafood superstar Rick Stein brings his best squid game. Who will end up sleeping with the fishes in a chaotic aquatic 2-part challenge?

episodes.name: John Dory - Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants must push the boat out to hook the catch of the day as Australia's top chef Josh Niland reels them in with his unique skills, before setting a gnarly John Dory Mystery Box challenge.

episodes.name: Luke Nguyen - Pressure Test
episodes.overview: One contender will be shafted as a saucy twist with a standout ingredient ensures stiff competition between the bottom three, who must replicate iconic chef Luke Nguyen's zesty pho without a recipe.

episodes.name: Two Course Root Veg - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Australia's homegrown superstar Curtis Stone visits the MasterChef kitchen to mentor and motivate two teams facing off in a massive Service Challenge to create next level root vegetable dishes.

episodes.name: Condiment Cook-off - Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: It's a golden opportunity to relish in Curtis' Condiment Cook-off. Today's tastiest condiment wins its maker Immunity, plus their creation will be on Coles supermarket shelves Australia-wide tomorrow!

episodes.name: Ingredient Gamble - Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Australia's most beloved food icon, Maggie Beer, is in the kitchen to spread the joy and inspire a full field of black apron contestants as they compete in a two-round Elimination Challenge.

episodes.name: Surprise Inside - Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: A Mystery Box Challenge allows our top nine to turn the tables on Jock, Andy and Melissa. It's what's inside that counts as our home cooks try to surprise the judges.

episodes.name: Peter Rabbit Garden - Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Chef Nelly Robinson presents Mr McGregor Garden - a whimsical dish that sends three home cooks down a tricky Pressure Test rabbit hole. For one unlucky contestant there will be no fairytale ending.

episodes.name: NGV Greek - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Greece is the word! The National Gallery of Victoria's Temple of Boom is the Herculean setting where food will be given the Midas touch in a big fat Greek Service Challenge odyssey with a twist. Opa!

episodes.name: Beat The Chef - Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: For a hot shot at an Immunity Pin, the lucky mug to grind out the best sweet coffee dish moves on to stir things up in a tea for two brewhaha against The Ritz-Carlton's perky pastry chef Kay-Lene Tan.

episodes.name: Colours - Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: It's a colour palette for the palate with a pearler of a taste test to set the tone. Who will then be caught red-handed and feeling blue cooking an elimination dish that highlights one chosen colour.

episodes.name: Everything Box - Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants must include every ingredient in the dreaded Everything Box to plate up a meal with the whole shebang. The makers of the bottom three dishes will face tomorrow's mind-blowing Pressure Test

episodes.name: Clare Smith Pie - Pressure Test
episodes.overview: Internationally renowned chef Clare Smyth of Sydney's Oncore Restaurant is here to put contestants through their Pressure Test paces with a complex dish inspired by beef, oyster and Irish stout pie.

episodes.name: Foraging - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: At the beautiful grounds of the O.MY Farm, contestants are split into 3 teams of 2. After foraging for one ingredient to hero in a dish, only THEN do they find out what course they’ll be cooking!

episodes.name: Aural Pleasure - Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Hear ye, hear ye! It's crunch time in a cracker of an Immunity Challenge. Judges are listening for the loudest, most rip-roaring dish that offers both aural pleasure and sizzling taste.

episodes.name: Kirsten Tibballs - Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Consummate pastry chef and chocolatier Kirsten Tibballs is here to set a sweet Elimination Challenge over two rounds. Who will pud up some patisserie magic and who will dessert the kitchen?

episodes.name: Freshness - Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: With an open garden, open pantry and an open mind, freshness will be front and centre as our top five let their imaginations run wild competing for a spot in the next Immunity Challenge.

episodes.name: Time Auction - Pressure Test
episodes.overview: A road trip to All Saints Estate in the Murray offers a high-stakes showdown with a classic Time Auction. A bidding war for ingredients is just the opening salvo in a battle for a shot at Immunity.

episodes.name: Fiesta - Pressure Test
episodes.overview: We're at the pointy end in cactus country, and the most succulent Mexican dish will earn its maker a stab at Immunity. Needles to say, the winner will be dancing a salsa in this thorny alfresco fiesta.

episodes.name: Stick Shed - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Our judges face their toughest decision yet in a service challenge at the incredible Stick Shed in Murtoa. Who will separate the wheat from the chaff in our grain event and be first into Finals Week?

episodes.name: Anchovies & Dijon Mustard - Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: An all-out anchovy assault and a ding-dong Dijon duel sees contestants pitted against each other in pairs for the first elimination round, with the bottom two duking it out to remain in the competition.

episodes.name: Tear-jerker - Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: Emotions run high with a semifinal spot at stake, as contestants feel the love in a tear-jerker of a Mystery Box. Hearts and souls will go into a MasterChef version of their family's favourite dish.

episodes.name: Peter Gilmore - Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Bennelong Restaurant's Peter Gilmore demonstrates how to create an intricate and tasty seafood dish. With no recipe, contestants must use total recall to perfectly replicate the dish or be eliminated.

episodes.name: Curtis Stone - Finals Advantage
episodes.overview: The final three must keep up with Curtis Stone as he whips up a magnificent beef dish. The contestant whose plate most closely resembles Curtis' creation will earn a whopping advantage for the semifinal.

episodes.name: Final 3 - Service Challenge
