episodes.overview: Our top three must create an entree, main course and dessert for a hungry crowd of diners and judges. The two contestants with the most exciting overall menu will earn their ticket into the grand finale.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: It's the Grand Finale, and whichever cook scores the most points across two rounds will lift the trophy aloft, claiming $250,000 in prize money and the title of MasterChef Australia winner, 2023!?

15.name: Secrets & Surprises
15.overview:
Returning for its 15th season, MasterChef Australia is back to deliver a series full of twists and turns with Secrets & Surprises.

Originally scheduled to premiere 1 May 2023, the series was postponed due to the sudden passing of judge Jock Zonfrillo the night before.

episodes.name: Series Premiere: Identity Dish
episodes.overview: It's a new era for MasterChef Australia as  Andy Allen welcomes three new judges: Sofia Levin, Poh Ling Yeow and Jean-Christophe Novelli, plus guest judge Jamie Oliver. The contestants were tasked to create a dish that represents them. The winner will win the only immunity pin of the season and a trip to London to work at Jamie Oliver's latest restaurant for a week.

episodes.name: Jamie Oliver's Team Service Challenge
episodes.overview: It's Day Two in the MasterChef Kitchen and already the 22 contestants are thrown into their first big Service Challenge, with Jamie Oliver running the kitchen.

episodes.name: Finger Food Invention Test
episodes.overview: Before our contestants can cook for immunity, they must get through Sofia's 'wrap your hands around this' challenge.

episodes.name: Time Versus Ingredients Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The first immunity challenge and it's a battle of time vs. ingredients. Five contestants must choose between one ingredient and a 90-minute cook, OR up to 20 ingredients but only 45 minutes to cook.

episodes.name: Food Dreams Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The first elimination of the season tasks the cooks with 75 minutes on the clock to create a dish representing their food dream.

episodes.name: Jamie Oliver's Parents Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: Our cooks are set for the challenge of making a dish from Mystery Box ingredients chosen by Jamie Oliver's parents, with the four weakest dishes set to send their makers into tomorrow's elimination.

episodes.name: Cook with Jamie Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: In this elimination cook the contestants are challenged to 'Keeping Up With Jamie' on an Oliver Family recipe in order to keep their place in the competition.

episodes.name: Queen Victoria Market Street Food Immunity Team Challenge
episodes.overview: The contestants cook for Immunity in a Team Challenge at the iconic Queen Victoria Night Market.

episodes.name: Inspired by Family Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Andy's mum Maree is in the kitchen to set an elimination challenge inspired by some of the Allen household's classic retro dishes. Contestants must make them MasterChef worthy, or risk going home.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge with a Twist!
episodes.overview: Today's Mystery Box comes with a twist, as our four judges throw in a secret ingredient that our cooks will have to wrangle.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Jack In The Box
episodes.overview: Judge Jean-Christophe Novelli sets the first Pressure Test of the competition with his 1992 dessert, 'Jack in the Box'.

episodes.name: Two Round Team Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: In Round 1, one 'champion' per team cooks, with the winner of Round 1 then taking their teammates into Round 2, and out into the garden to cook for Immunity.

episodes.name: One Inch Cube Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: In today's two round elimination, our contestants' palettes are challenged with the classic One-inch cube taste test, which sees six favorites, cook for their spot in the competition.

episodes.name: French Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: A French-themed Mystery Box in Bendigo, regional Victoria, challenges the contestants to create 'magnifique' dishes.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Liam Downes' Smoked Egg Yolk Raviolo, Truffle & Asparagus
episodes.overview: Nat, Gillian, Alex and Lourdes battle it out in a Pressure Test set by Chef Liam Downes at Black Cat Truffles just outside Ballarat.

episodes.name: Heirloom Tomato Team Relay
episodes.overview: It's the chaotic, colourful and feared race that is the MasterChef Team Relay! Today, in teams of four, cooks will tag-team their way to hopefully plate a cohesive dish and win immunity.

episodes.name: Luke Nguyen Ingredient Gamble Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The three losing teams faced a two-round elimination challenge set by Luke Nguyen. In round one each contestant was assigned a pair of ingredients, one visible and the other hidden underneath a cloche, and 75 minutes to cook a dish with the ingredient of their choosing.

episodes.name: Vincent Yeow Lim Wok Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: All of the contestants competed in a mystery box challenge set by guest judge, chef and social media presenter Vincent Yeow Lim, who asked them to create a dish in 75 minutes using a wok.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Anna Polyviou's Sunny Side Up
episodes.overview: The bottom four contestants were given three hours to re-create chef Anna Polyviou's sunny side up dessert.

episodes.name: Microwave Hack Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: The judges task our contestants to create an immunity worthy dish in 75 minutes, using one of their four microwave hacks.

episodes.name: Egg Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Inspired by a visit from viral sensation Mikiko Terasaki, contestants must creatively use eggs in a dish to avoid elimination.

episodes.name: Asian Sauces Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: A mystery box challenge with a saucy twist. The cooks must use at least one of six Asian sauces to cook a showstopping dish, with the bottom four headed for tomorrow's pressure test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Darren Purchese's Cherry Blossom
episodes.overview: MasterChef legend Darren Purchese returns with another diabolical dessert, which will spell the end of the competition for one talented cook.

episodes.name: Second Chance Cook
episodes.overview: Eight eliminated contestants return for the chance to cook their way back into the competition.

episodes.name: Rick Stein's Seafood Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: King of the sea, Rick Stein is here, and the contestants are excited cooking for such an icon. Over two rounds, seafood is on the menu but for one cook, it will be their last time in the kitchen.

episodes.name: Pub Food Service Challenge
episodes.overview: Contestants face off in a team service challenge where they are tasked with elevating traditional pub food.

episodes.name: Cook with Curtis Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: The losing team from the pub challenge must cook along with legendary chef Curtis Stone as he creates his Spice Rubbed Pork, Smoked Beetroot and Hasselback Potatoes.

episodes.name: Sauce Immunity Challenge
episodes.overview: Today's challenge is to combine two nations' cuisines into a tasty dish. There is a huge prize on the line: the winning sauce will be made available to buy in Coles stores around the country.

episodes.name: Plant-Based Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: Tonight's elimination is a plant-based challenge. Contestants create a well-known meat dish using only plant-based ingredients for their chance to secure the Top 10 of MasterChef 2024.

episodes.name: Adriano Zumbo's Jelly Mystery Box Challenge
episodes.overview: Sweet Week has arrived! Adriano Zumbo is here as a guest judge and kicks things off with a wobbly jelly Mystery Box. Contestants compete to make a perfect shaky sweet to win precious immunity.

episodes.name: The Croquembouche Invention Test
episodes.overview: Sweet Week continues as Adriano Zumbo sets a challenge that puts a new twist on a classic. The cooks must interpret the croquembouche in their own unique way.

episodes.name: Twins Challenge
episodes.overview: It's the iconic twin's challenge. Each team must utilize an appliance in their 90-minute dessert cook, aiming for identical dishes, despite only being able to shout instructions at each other.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Taste Test
episodes.overview: Two tough rounds will test our cooks. First, Adriano Zumbo's Macaron Taste Test, and then a coffee-inspired dessert cook, with the weakest dish seeing its maker eliminated from the competition.

episodes.name: Mystery Box Challenge: Most Ingredients Ever
episodes.overview: Tonight's mega Mystery Box features the most ingredients ever, the cooks have just 30 minutes to pull off a winning dish, with the bottom three sending their makers into tomorrow's Pressure Test

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Hugh Allen
episodes.overview: Hugh Allen returns to the MasterChef kitchen to set a pressure test merging classic French techniques with flavours of the Australian bush

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Bacon & Eggs
episodes.overview: The contestants battle it out to reinvent the classic bacon and eggs. The stakes are high today, the top dish will win an epic mystery prize, but the bottom dish will be eliminated

episodes.name: Mystery Box: Hong Kong
episodes.overview: MasterChef Australia is in Hong Kong! The first challenge is a Hong Kong style Mystery Box. Today the judges are looking for the top three cooks to progress into tomorrow's immunity challenge

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Vicky Cheng
episodes.overview: After a demonstration from Michelin starred chef Vicky Cheng, three cooks must recreate his dish, from memory alone, the winner claiming immunity from this week's elimination

episodes.name: Service Challenge: Street Food
episodes.overview: The cooks are split into three teams, cooking street food in a traditional dai pai dong. They must prepare a two-dish menu, using either a wok, steamer or deep fryer, catering for 120 hungry locals

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Lucky Dip
episodes.overview: Today's Hong Kong Immunity Challenge. A Lucky Dip proves fortunate for some, challenging for others. With two randomly picked ingredients, each contestant must perfectly pair them to create a dish

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: Ingredient Auction
episodes.overview: Contestants bid against one another, trading time for ingredients in a MasterChef classic. Four contestants compete to cook a dish that helps them avoid elimination and secure their place in the top 6.

episodes.name: Mystery Box: Poh's Everything
episodes.overview: Contestants must cook a dish using all nine ingredients in Poh's Everything Mystery Box. The winner will score themselves $5,000 to spend at Harvey Norman.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Guillaume Brahimi
episodes.overview: Chef Guillaume Brahimi has brought a pressure test dish that will push the contestants to their limits. They need to replicate the dish as closely as possible... but they must plate up 5 serves.

episodes.name: Immunity Challenge: Family Food Heroes
episodes.overview: Emotions run high as the top five open chests, revealing treasured photos of their family food heroes. Inspired by their photos, each cook fights for their final shot at immunity.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge: The World's Most Extreme Ingredients
episodes.overview: Tonight, the contestants face off with some of the world's most extreme ingredients. These ingredient 'beasts' are the spiciest, sweetest, most sour, most bitter and most pungent on offer.

episodes.name: Mystery Box: Golden Ticket
episodes.overview: The mystery boxes contain a golden ticket which will fast track the contestant with the top dish into the semi-final, while the other three will have to battle it out in tomorrow's pressure test.

episodes.name: Pressure Test: Josh Niland
episodes.overview: Internationally renowned chef Josh Niland pushes the contestants to their limits with a unique dish from his acclaimed restaurant, St. Peter. They must each recreate his dish as closely as possible.

episodes.name: The Judges Become The Cooks!
episodes.overview: Andy, Poh and Jean Christophe swap roles, becoming the cooks while the Semi-Finalists become the judges'. The fun doesn't stop there, as our Semi-Finalists must then take on the judges in a relay

episodes.name: Final 3 - Service Challenge
episodes.overview: With Curtis Stone's help, our Semi-Finalists must each prepare a three-course meal for 20 diners and the judges.

episodes.name: Episode 50
episodes.overview: Our two Grand Finalists go head-to-head over two rounds to see who will be crowned the winner of MasterChef Australia 2024!

16.name: Season 16
16.overview: This season feature 4 judges. Andy Allen, Sofia Levin, Jean-Christophe Novelli and Poh Ling Yeow. The number of contestants increased from 18 to 22. Like the previous 2 seasons, the season omitted the broadcast of the audition stage. Only one Immunity Pin is up for grabs this season.
